title: fluffy pancakes with strawberry-orange sauce
directions: Place the strawberries, orange juice concentrate, lemon juice and lemon zest in a blender or food processor; blend until smooth. If using fresh strawberries that are not very sweet, you may want to add a little sugar to the sauce at this point.
If you do, blend the sauce briefly to distribute the sugar.
Set aside.

title: cast-iron skillet biscuits(another great biscuit recipe!)
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon Crisco in cast-iron skillet at 500° in oven. Blend dry ingredients and cut in 2 tablespoons Crisco. Mix buttermilk in with a fork.
Knead lightly.
Pat out in flour. Cut with cutter.
Put in frypan. Turn to coat.
Bake 10 minutes at 500°.

title: apple snack cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg, blending well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in chopped pecans and apple.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash, pare and slice thin the raw potatoes.
Arrange in layers in a greased baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper; dust lightly with flour.
Dot with butter.
After all potatoes have been used, add enough milk to come within 1 inch of top of the potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 2 hours.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Mix all together and let stand 15 minutes.
Pour in baking dish and bake about 40 minutes at 350° or until as brown as you want.
Do not overbake.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and shape with wet hands.
Cook in electric skillet with tomato soup, tomato sauce, water and seasoning to taste (ex. thyme, savory, rosemary, sage).
Heat to boiling (300 to 350°) and turn down to simmer 20 to 30 minutes until done.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: In small saucepan add milk, onion, potatoes, margarine, salt and
pepper.
Cook	on medium heat about 5 minutes, then add
crab meat, Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle flour gradually, stirring.
Simmer
for 20 minutes or until potatoes are cooked. Stir often to keep from sticking.
Serve hot.
(Great made with the claw meat.)

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and sugar.
Stir in cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add nuts, if desired. Fold in Cool Whip (do not whip or beat).
Pour into mold and freeze, preferably overnight.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together; drop by tablespoon onto greased griddle or pan. Cook 3 minutes on each side.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add everything else in a big bowl. Bake uncovered in a Pammed or greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
This recipe is fast, easy and very good.

title: sumptuous broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, onion, sunflower seeds and raisins in large bowl.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; blend well with wire whisk.
Pour over broccoli mix and cover in refrigerator until chilled.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steak;
brown in oil.
Drain off fat. Place
meat in crock-pot with onion on top.
Mix seasonings
with tomato sauce and pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low
setting 8 or more hours.
Add a small amount of water if necessary.
Serve with noodles or spaghetti.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Grated cabbage and onions together.
Mix vinegar, vegetable oil, sugar, mustard, celery seed together.
Heat until sugar is melted, do not boil.
Put cabbage and onions in a bowl layered with 1 cup sugar.
Pour heated mixture over cabbage.
Cover and let stand in refrigerated for 3 days.
Really good.

title: confetti dip
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and vinegar over low heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and softened cream cheese.
Stir until smooth with small mixer.
Add the onion, pepper and pimento.
Add dash of Tabasco sauce.
Stir until mixed well and let set in refrigerator until cooled.

title: lasagna
directions: Add first 8 ingredients and simmer for 40 minutes.
While sauce is simmering, cook noodles.
Mix cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese together.
In a 9 x 12-inch dish, pour 1/3 of sauce, cheese, then noodles.
Layer until gone.
Save cheese for top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350°.

title: coconut custard
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: In a crock-pot or large pot on stove on medium heat, put navy beans and juice in with ham and onion.

title: favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter until creamy. Gradually beat in peanut butter, brown sugar, then granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs, then vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour and baking soda; gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Press balls down with a fork, making a crisscross pattern on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then transfer to racks to cool completely.
Store airtight.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni using the least amount of water version on the box.
Cool.
Add artichokes, onions, celery, olives and water chestnuts.
Add mayonnaise mixture.
Mix well and chill.

title: green chili salsa
directions: Peel and coarsely chop tomatoes. Combine all ingredients in a 6-quart kettle. Bring to boil, cover and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes. Ladle into pint jars, wipe rims, seal, and process in boiling water bath for 45 minutes. Makes 8 pints.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except powdered sugar. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. While hot, roll in powdered sugar. Let cool; roll in sugar again.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cheese in boiling water.
Blend with mixer. Add marshmallows, pineapple and 7-Up.
Chill until almost firm. Then fold in Dream Whip and chill until firm.
I pour this into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Put on baking board; rub the sugar with heel of hand.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve alone or on toasted English muffins.
May add cooked macaroni and extra mayonnaise for Macaroni Seafood Salad.

title: chicken atop rice(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) glass baking dish, combine rice, mushrooms, celery, soup and milk; mix well.
Cut larger pieces of chicken in half for uniform size.
Arrange on top or rice, skin-side up.
Sprinkle with salt, paprika and poultry seasoning. Cook, covered with wax paper, 28 minutes or until chicken is done. Serves 5 to 6.

title: banana-oatmeal cookies(this is a good breakfast cookie.)
directions: I don't have a chocolate chip cookie recipe, other than adding chocolate chips to my Butter/Sugar Cookie recipe.
I have found that the best chocolate chip cookie recipe is on the Nestle chocolate chips package.
Those Toll House cookies can't be beat!

title: cheese cake
directions: Spread crescent rolls on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to shortening mixture and mix well.
Add water, vanilla and oats and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Yields approximately 9 dozen.

title: daddy's homemade ice cream
directions: Put gelatine and sugar in top of double boiler, not over heat; mix thoroughly.
Stir in milk and place over boiling water.
Stir constantly until gelatine
is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
To hot milk mixture, add beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add cream and proceed with freezing.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: chicken divan
directions: Partially cook broccoli (about 5 minutes).
Arrange chicken in a well-greased baking dish.
Arrange broccoli over chicken.

title: cranberry glazed pork roast
directions: In a small saucepan, stir all ingredients together except the pork. Cook, stirring over medium heat, until thickened. Set aside. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Spoon 1/2 cup glaze over roast and continue to bake for 30 to 45 minutes more. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serve with remainder of sauce.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain. Brown beef in butter; stir in tomato sauce, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter shallow 9-inch round baking dish.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Prepare 9-inch tube pan before starting.
Heat together applesauce, shortening, raisins and sugars in saucepan.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ground cloves in mixing bowl.
When applesauce mixture is good and hot, pour over flour mixture and stir quickly.
Add chopped nuts.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper. In another bowl, beat eggs and milk. In a third bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Coat chicken with flour mixture. Dip in egg mixture, then roll in crumb mixture. Place in a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 55 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: quick and easy blender custard
directions: In blender combine all ingredients.
Mix on highest speed on blender for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into custard dishes coated with vegetable oil.
Sprinkle tops of custard with cinnamon and nutmeg. Place custard dishes in hollow pan of hot water about 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: orange snow salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions on box.
Chill to heavy syrupy texture.
Fold in cottage cheese.
Add Mandarin oranges and Cool Whip, mixing well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill well.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix cheese and beat well until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Add 7-Up and blend well.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over carrots. Refrigerate 2 to 3 days.

title: "want more" salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour over remaining combined ingredients. Toss and serve. Calories per serving: 155; 6 grams of fat. Time involved:
20 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop cabbage,
tomatoes,
peppers and onions.
Mix with salt and let stand
to
hours.
Drain and remove as much water as possible.
Boil
vinegar, water, sugar and spices for 5 minutes. Add
chopped
vegetable
mixture.
Bring to a boil and pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak the cukes, onions and peppers in salt water for 1 hour; rinse and drain.
Cook (simmer) with the remaining ingredients for 20 minutes and seal in jars.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a deep 2 to 3-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; stir. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in baking soda.
Pour immediately on a greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: "chunky guacamole"
directions: Halve avocados and remove pits. Cut into small cubes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.

title: cornflake indian pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Stir once in a while. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: applesauce cake(sugarless)
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and water in saucepan.
Cook until fruit is soft and water is evaporated; set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine eggs, applesauce, Equal, oil and vanilla.
Add nuts and fruit mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana delight
directions: Make crumbs of first 4 ingredients.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes in 375° oven. (Watch carefully.)
Place half of mixture in bottom of 9x13 inch pan.
Slice 3 bananas over crumbs. Mix pudding with milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Add ice cream and blend well.
Pour over bananas.
Top with 3 more bananas and remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes. Squeeze out liquid. Add other ingredients and mix well. Fry by spoonfuls in hot grease. Brown on both sides and drain on paper towel.

title: cheese potatoes casserole
directions: Pare and slice potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add bacon, onion, cheese and butter.
Place all ingredients on large piece of foil; seal and place in Pyrex dish.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Then spread over a split loaf of French bread.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Slice and serve warm.

title: monkey bread
directions: With scissors, cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Shake pieces in bag of cinnamon and sugar.
Place pieces of biscuits in well-greased tube pan, putting chopped nuts in between layers. Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done.
Peel and dice in large bowl.
Dice onion and eggs.
Add to hot potatoes.
Add pickles, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Salt to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Add salt to boiling water and let cool.
Pour over cucumbers and leave 2 weeks.
Wash off brine.
Use enough cold water to cover cucumbers.
Add alum and leave 24 hours.
Drain and discard alum water.
Pour enough cold vinegar over cucumbers to cover and add mixed pickling spice.
Leave 24 hours.
Drain and discard.
Add 3 cups sugar after discarding vinegar.
After 24 hours, add 3 more cups sugar.
Add 3 more cups sugar after another 24 hours.
Syrup will rise to cover pickles as sugar dissolves.
Store in glass jars.
Jars do not have to be sealed.

title: lima bean barbecue
directions: Add salt
to
beans and cook until tender.
Drain.
Fry sausage
until
brown.
Mix
all
ingredients
except sausage. Place half of bean mixture in 1 1/2 quart size casserole dish. Cover with	half
of sausages.
Add remaining bean mixture and sausages.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: borsch(may prepare ahead.  serves 6 to 8.)
directions: Finely chop drained beets, but reserve the juice.
Combine with beet juice, bouillon, water and minced onion.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Serve hot or cold topped with sour cream.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Prepare beef, onion and green pepper; brown and stir in tomatoes, paste, oregano, garlic, salt, pepper and 1 cup spaghetti.
In a large bowl, toss hot spaghetti with oil; set aside 1 cup of the spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese and eggs to the tossed spaghetti.
Press into a 10-inch pie plate.
Spoon cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Spoon beef mixture over the cottage cheese.
Cover loosely with greased foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese; continue baking for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, then in a separate bowl mix together next 5 ingredients.
Mix well and add to flour mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Stir in noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon immediately onto wax paper or foil.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch or 10-inch pie plate.
Place sliced apples in plate.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add flour; mix and spread over apples. Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Put oats, brown sugar, flour and salt into a bowl and stir thoroughly.
Melt butter; let it get quite hot, but not bubble. Stir butter into oat mixture until sugar is melted.
Add slightly beaten egg and vanilla.
Stir all together.
Drop very small amounts from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 7 minutes at 375°.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Combine the vegetables in a large pot and add 1 1/2-quart water. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Pour immediately into hot jars, leaving 1-inch at the top. Add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart jar and 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint jar. Process pints for 55 minutes and quarts for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: italian antipasto salad
directions: Cook and drain shells.
Season with garlic powder and garlic salt; add oregano, salt and pepper.
Add green pepper, onion, salami, ham, cheese, pepperoni, celery, olives and mix with dressing mix (follow directions on package).
Refrigerate overnight.
Add more dressing in morning if needed.

title: filled pears
directions: Peel and cut pears into halves.
Steam until tender in a small amount of water.
Cool.
Chop dried fruits.
Spoon into pears.
May be served with tablespoon of sour cream sweetened with artificial sweetener.

title: grandma's rhubarb cobbler
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, toss rhubarb, sugar and nutmeg.
Put over first cake mix layer.
Add rest of cake batter.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with half and half cream.

title: seafood stuffed shells
directions: Prepare macaroni shells.
Chill 1 hour.
Place cottage cheese, milk, lemon juice, salt and pepper in blender.
Cover.
Blend on high, stop occasionally to scrape sides, about 2 minutes.
Remove and reserve 1/2 cup.
Add parsley and basil to blender.
Cover. Blend on high for 45 seconds, until smooth.
Chill.

title: almond brie pie
directions: Unroll 1 package of crescent rolls to fit bottom of 9 or 10-inch pie pan, pressing seams closed.
Roast almonds in margarine at 250° until light brown.
Cut Brie and place in pie pan.
Pour almonds and margarine over Brie.
Cover with second package of crescent rolls.
Trim edge of pie pan and decorate top with trimmings.
Bake at 325° until light browned.
Cool for 40 minutes before serving.
Remove from pie pan to serving plate.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, tapioca, water, butter and 3 mashed peaches.
Cook on low heat (or simmer) for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sliced peaches.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix lightly the meat, egg, bread crumbs, minced onions, evaporated milk and salt.
Form into meatballs, about 1 teaspoon each.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: sweet corn and basmati rice salad(8 servings)
directions: Whisk red wine vinegar and mustard in large bowl to blend. Gradually whisk in 1/2 cup oil.
Season vinaigrette to taste with salt and pepper
Using sharp knife, cut corn kernels from cobs. Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add green onions, saute 30 seconds.
Add corn; saute until corn is crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. (Vinaigrette and corn mixture can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover separately; chill.
Re-warm corn mixture over medium heat and re-whisk vinaigrette before using.)

title: fermented fruit and fermented fruit friendship cake
directions: Do not drain fruit.
Combine peaches, 2 1/2 cups sugar and yeast in a one gallon glass or crockery jar with loose fitting lid; stir to mix.
Stir daily for 10 days.
On the 10th day add the pineapple and 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir daily for 10 more days. Add cherries, fruit cocktail and remaining sugar and stir daily for 10 more days.
Drain fruit, reserving juice for the next batch.
Makes enough fruit for 4 cakes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Crush bag of chips into small pieces.
Line bottom of pan with chips, saving a little of the chips.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: pennsylvania pot pie
directions: Place stewing chicken, onion and 1 teaspoon salt in a large pot; cover with water.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth; pick meat from bones, then return meat to broth.
Add potatoes and cook for about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting(very chocolatey)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and cool.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: raisin spice drops
directions: Pour enough boiling water over raisins to cover them.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Drain raisins, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Dissolve soda in this liquid.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with raisin liquid; blend well.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: marinated zucchini
directions: Slice the zucchini lengthwise into thick slices.
Fry the zucchini slices in a heavy skillet to brown them.
Drain them on a paper towel.
Layer garlic, sage and zucchini in a large jar.
Add 2 tablespoons of warm oil to the jar.
Add vinegar or half parts wine and vinegar to almost fill the jar.
Add the hot pepper. Refrigerate overnight.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; toss with apples and set aside.

In large bowl, beat oil, sugar and eggs. In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt. Alternately add flour mixture and orange juice to creamed mixture. Generously grease a Bundt pan with shortening.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into pan then 1/2 of apples; repeat layers, then top with remaining batter.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or orange glaze made with powdered sugar and orange juice.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 10 biscuits.

title: lo-fat holiday applesauce nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices together and combine with first ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread into oiled or sprayed and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: deluxe chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large pot or dutch oven.
Add water to cover, onion, bay leaf, peppercorns and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Cool chicken in broth.
Drain, reserving broth for another use. Shred chicken with 2 forks or with your fingers.
Mix shredded chicken, chopped onion, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Taste and add salt if needed.
Set aside.
In blender or food processor, combine green chiles, tomatoes, cilantro, whipping cream and egg.
Blend until smooth.
Add salt to taste. Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a small skillet. with tongs, carefully place 1 tortilla at a time in hot oil.
Hold in oil for 3 to 5 seconds until softened.
Quickly turn tortilla and soften other side, 3 to 5 seconds.
Drain over skillet or on paper towels.
Place 1/8 of the chicken mixture on each tortilla, pressing the mixture to make it compact.
Roll tightly and sprinkle evenly with 1 cup shredded cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake 20 minutes, or until heated through and bubbly.
Makes 8 enchiladas.

title: german pickled herring in sour cream
directions: Mix sour cream, apples, onion, pickle and sugar in a medium size non-aluminum bowl.
Gently stir in herring.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours or up to 5 days.
Serves 12; only 60 cents per serving.
Contains 162 calories and 11 grams fat.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: peaches n cream pie
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 10-inch pie pan.
Combine first seven ingredients and pour into pan.
Drain peaches, reserving 3 tablespoons juice; spread peaches on mixture in pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice in small bowl; beat at medium speed for two minutes.
Spoon to within one inch of edge of batter.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: harvest pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Fold whipped topping into filling mixture.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Sprinkle with apples, pecans and marshmallows just before serving.
Drizzle caramel sauce over pie.

title: broccoli cheese quiche
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Toss with margarine.
Place in bottom of pie crust.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese mixed with flour. Beat eggs and evaporated milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 375° approximately 60 minutes or until set in center.
You may have to cover your crust toward the end to prevent overbrowning.
Real men even eat this quiche!

title: christmas plum bread(double batch)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt in large bowl. Add eggs, oil, plums, food coloring and vanilla; mix well. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done. May add to warm bread 1 1/3 cups sugar plus 1 cup lemon juice (boiled).

title: graduation party punch
directions: Pour lemonade into punch bowl.
Stir in berries.
Just before serving, mix in ginger ale and ice cubes.
Drop in sherbet by spoonfuls or small balls made with ice cream dipper.

title: freezing corn
directions: Mix and cook 10 minutes.
Cool and freeze.

title: ham stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice from top of tomatoes.
Scoop inside out with a grapefruit knife or spoon.
Invert and drain on paper towels while making the fillings.
Combine the ham and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill tomatoes and refrigerate until served.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix sugar, water, cinnamon, salt and vanilla. Cover and bring to a soft-ball boil stage. Let set for a few minutes. Add pecans and separate on waxed paper. Toast pecans in the oven for 8 minutes at 350°. Easy!!!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, squash and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: apple pudding
directions: Mix together the flour, shortening and sugar.
Add baking powder, salt and enough milk to make soft, not sticky, dough. Grate the apples.
Roll out dough; sprinkle apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in Pyrex dish that has 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar dissolved in it.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oven hashed brown potatoes
directions: Grease a 9 x 6-inch baking dish.
Place potatoes in saucepan. Add boiling salted water to half cover them.
Cover and boil for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain, cool, then peel and cube.
Place in baking dish.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Saute onions for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over potatoes.
Stir with fork to mix.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 1 hour.
Just before serving, place under broiler for a few minutes to brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: glazed nuts
directions: In 2-quart saucepan mix sugar, orange juice, corn syrup and salt.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Take off heat and add pecans. Stir until creamy.
Pour onto wax paper and separate.

title: garden style lasagna
directions: In a skillet, brown ground chuck; drain and set aside.
Slice the mushrooms and prepare frozen spinach according to directions on the package.
Drain thoroughly.
In a large, deep skillet, simmer mushrooms, tomato, onion, spinach, pepper, garlic and bell pepper until tender.
Add meat.
This helps flavors blend.
While vegetables simmer, cook lasagna noodles according to directions on the package.
Drain noodles.

title: grandmother's "t" cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Blend dry ingredients.
Work with spoon until crumbly.
Roll in hands into balls and mash flat or roll out and cut.
Bake at 350°.

title: ratatouille
directions: About 1 hour before serving, drain tomatoes, reserving juice; set both aside.

In large bowl toss remaining ingredients until vegetables are well coated. In ovenproof deep skillet over high heat, heat 1/2 cup water and reserved tomato juice to boiling. Add coated vegetables and top with tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and continue cooking until liquid is reduced and vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix pumpkin with eggs. To butter mixture, add alternately eggs and pumpkin with the dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased loaf pans; bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes.

title: no-crust fruit pie
directions: Place apples in Pyrex dish and sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Combine egg, sugar, flour and margarine.
Pour over bread slices and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until done.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Boil marinade together
a few minutes and pour over broccoli. If over raw broccoli, set 12 to 24 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1/2 cup of butter.
Add flour, broth and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil mixed vegetables according to directions.
In a casserole dish add sauce, chicken and vegetables, mix.
Cover top with bread crumbs mixed with 1/4 cup butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until hot.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add pork and beans, tomatoes, salt and sugar.
Pour 1/2 mixture in a baking dish; add layer of onion. Add remaining mixture.
Top with the bacon slices and sprinkle top with a little brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: In blender, put drained artichoke hearts; blend for 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Place in ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips and crackers.

title: creamed cucumber salad
directions: Mix sour cream, vinegar, sugar and milk until creamy.
Pour over cucumbers and onions and stir.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove meat from bones.
Chop into bite size pieces.
In long casserole dish, put chicken in bottom.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple with a punch(non alcoholic party punch)
directions: The night before the party, pour some of the club soda into a ring mold.
Freeze.
As the liquid mold begins to harden, add the maraschino cherries.
Freeze.

title: wanda cake
directions: Mix together all the ingredients in a small baking dish.
Cook at 315° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raspberry jello mold
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O in 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water. Chill until partially set.
Cream the cream cheese with coffee cream.
(You can use milk.)
Add powdered sugar and vanilla. Combine with Jell-O and pour into a large mold.
Chill until firm. Mix raspberry Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add frozen raspberries, which have been thawed.
Pour over first mixture and chill until firm.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: On each chicken breast, place a piece of the ham and cheese. Put a little bit of the sauce on top of the ham and cheese.
Roll the chicken breast up, using toothpicks to secure if necessary. Mix the bread crumbs with the Parmesan cheese.
Dip the chicken in the egg and roll in the bread crumb mixture.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or microwave 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oriental barbecue marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Rub it well into the meat. Put in refrigerator for 2 hours. Toss meat every 1/2 hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Add mashed banana.
Then add all dry ingredients (nuts optional).
Pour into pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add enough second part to make batter like cake.

title: honey mustard pretzels
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour over pretzels, coating well.
Place on aluminum foil, shiny side down.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes, turning halfway.
Bake until not sticky from honey.

title: quickie sugar fudge
directions: In 1-quart glass casserole dish, add powdered sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and butter.
Microwave (High) 2 minutes, then stir until evenly mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts, blending well.
Line a pie plate with wax paper.
Pour fudge into plate; chill until firm. Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together.
Chill dough.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch closely.
Cookies are done even though they are still whitish.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Microwave chips for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High (100% power) until chips lose their shape when stirred.
Dip the large strawberries, one at a time, into chocolate to coat halfway. Place on wax paper to set.
Enjoy!

title: flour sack cookies
directions: This is a very old recipe.
It has no method but be sure to grease cookie sheet.
This cookie got the name "flour sack" because after it was baked the woman placed them in a cloth flour sack for storage and hung it from the rafters in the kitchen.
This served two purposes:
It kept out the insects and the children.

title: gaspacho ala k j
directions: Finely chop onions, celery, green peppers, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Prepare salad dressing mix according to package directions using half the oil called for in instructions.
Pour over prepared cut vegetables and marinate in refrigerator one hour. Add tomato juice and chill, covered, overnight or at least six hours.
Serves six.

title: kool-aid sherbet
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in milk; pour in freezer tray. Freeze until mushy; spoon into cold bowl.
Beat until smooth. Return to freezer tray; freeze for at least 2 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple, pie filling and nuts in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cake mix and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until crusty and golden.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, cheese, sour cream, chives, salt and pepper together and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly in bowl.
Stir in milk mixture, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Put bread into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour all ingredients over.
Stir gently.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry special
directions: Melt margarine; mix with crumbs, powdered sugar and nuts. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; let cool. Mix the cream cheese, eggs, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Top with blueberry pie filling and Cool whip.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, gelatin, salt and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until clear, stirring constantly. Cool.
Add prepared strawberries and spoon into pastry shell. Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole with topping
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 9-inch casserole.

title: frances' cheese straws
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add flour and salt; knead and blend. Roll into small balls or logs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Place on baking sheet; use back of fork dipped in flour to imprint them.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: cranapple punch
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Add all ingredients to crab meat.
Mix well.
Fill crab shells with the
mixture.	Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 320° until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: Ready to Cook Weight:
6 to 9 pounds; Total Cooking Time:
2 1/4 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: spicy pears
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover pan and simmer pears about 20 minutes or until they are tender.
Serve pears warm or chilled.
Serves 4.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, coconut, milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and gradually add flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition. Divide dough into two parts and shape into 2 rolls 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Roll in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Cut 1/4 inch slices.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: no roll sugar crinkles
directions: Cool in refrigerator.
Form into balls; dip in sugar and press down a little with palm of hand.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Stir well.
In unbaked pie shell, put pecans first, then pour your mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix bread crumbs, corn bread crumbs, onions, celery, sage, salt and pepper all together in a large bowl.
Then add hot broth and eggs.
Bake in a large pan at 350°.

title: apricot pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, salt, allspice and nutmeg.
In another bowl, mix baby food, sugar, eggs, oil and pecans.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for an hour or until cake tests done.

title: angel hair flans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 miniature muffin pans (approximately 1-inch cups, 12 per pan) with cooking spray.

title: aunt yvonne's brownies
directions: Blend the melted butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add the eggs; beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl. Gradually add this to the egg mixture.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from the edges of pan.
Cool; cut into squares. Chopped nuts or chocolate chips can be added before baking.

title: oh-so-good raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with hot water and soak for 15 minutes.
Drain. Separate eggs and beat yolks lightly.
Stir in vinegar, butter, spices, walnuts and raisins.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually beat in sugar.
Fold into raisin mixture.
Turn into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 45 minutes longer, or until pastry is browned and filling set.
(Crust browns quickly, so keep checking pie as it bakes.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat oil, eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add zucchini, pineapple and vanilla to creamy mixture.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Makes 2 large loaves and 1 small loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done; test with toothpick.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Brown meat; drain fat. Add seasoning mix, water and olives. Simmer 5 minutes. Place rolls flat to form a crust. Crush corn chips into tiny pieces. Add half to bottom (on top of crust). Add meat, sour cream, cheese and rest of corn chips. Cook 20 to 25 minutes. Can be served with salsa.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni with salt to taste according to package.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and pepper
(to taste), then add milk.
When white sauce is thick, add cubed cheese.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni in a baking dish; mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hard sauce
directions: Cream the butter.
Add the sugar, gradually creaming thoroughly.
Add the vanilla.
Chill.
Serve with Apple Brown Betty and steamed and bread puddings.

title: salsa
directions: Skin, core and chop tomatoes.
(I use a food processor.)
Chop onions, green peppers and chili peppers.
Put all in a pot; simmer until desired thickness (about 3 1/2 hours).
While still on stove simmering, put salsa in sterile jars and seal immediately.
Jars will seal on their own.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix together oats, flour and sugar until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in the bottom of a pan.
Slice cranberry sauce 1/2-inch thick.
Place slices on oat mixture.
Spread rest of oat mixture on top.
Place in oven and bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy carrot bars
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl; beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all up.
Use long thin casserole pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Last 15 minutes, crush chips or crumbs on top.
(Half recipe will serve 6 as it is rich.)

title: carolyn's oriental salad
directions: Bring 2 quarts of water to a boil; add the bean threads and bring back to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let stand for 2 minutes.
Then rinse until bean threads are cool, put into a large bowl and cut bean threads into smaller pieces.

title: chocolate eclair torte
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with one layer whole graham crackers.
Spread with 1/2 pudding mixture, one more layer crackers and rest of pudding.
Top with crackers.
Make frosting with 5 remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over top layer of crackers.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: puttin on the ritz
directions: Cook eagle brand milk and dates until thick as paste.
Add pecans.
Place small amount on crackers.
Place on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Enjoy.
Be careful and don't cook too long- will burn.

title: easy dinner casserole
directions: Rinse frozen peas and carrots under cold running water to separate.
Drain.
Mix peas, carrots and remaining ingredients except chips in ungreased 2-quart casserole or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash together with a fork: avocados, salad oil, garlic, salsa, tomato, lemon juice and onion.
Chill for 1 hour and serve with tortilla chips.

title: wild rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine until translucent.
Add rice and cook lightly.
Add mushrooms and juice, consomme and water.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour in casserole dish and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: ham and cheese brunch
directions: First Layer:
Cube bread and sprinkle in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute peppers and onions in olive oil.
Cook sausage.
Add sausage to green peppers and onions.
Add Italian bread crumbs. Remove stems from mushrooms.
Stuff with filling.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: homemade bread
directions: Scald milk, sugar and oleo together.
Let cool.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together and let foam appear to check that yeast is alive.
Add 2 cups of flour to milk mixture to make a thick paste. Beat eggs and add to milk-flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add remaining flour to make dough that can be kneaded; knead dough on a floured board.
Test amount of flour by not sticking to hands and if an indentation remains when fingers are punched into bread.

Let rest 10 minutes covered with a bowl. Grease a large bowl and roll bread around in bowl to coat dough. Cover with greased waxed paper and let rise until doubled in size. Punch down and let rest 20 minutes.
Form bread into loaves, rolls, cinnamon rolls or holiday rings.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes for loaves.

title: twistin' pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, blend Italian dressing, mustard and pepper. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover; chill thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mrs. brandon's dressing
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt as needed when meat is done.
Cool broth.
Add broth to crumbled up cornbread (not too mealy).
May add 1/4 cup Milnot or more, if needed, to make dressing thin.
Add sage and pepper.

title: sun-drop pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening real good.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add 1 egg at a time and cream well after each addition. Then add 1/2 of Sun-Drop; cream, then add 1/2 of flour; cream, and add the other 1/2 of Sun-Drop; cream.
Then add other 1/2 of flour. Cream after each addition; beat well.
Add flavoring; beat.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk.
Cook over medium heat; keep stirring until thickened and bubbling.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Pour chicken mixture into deep 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with flaky pastry; cut slits.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Combine flour and dry seasonings; blend into onion mixture.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and vinegar until smooth.
Add tomatoes and okra, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Serves 6.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until done, seasoning to taste with salt, pepper and onion.
Remove from broth; debone.
Cook vermicelli in the broth.
Add cheese and melt slowly in vermicelli/broth.
Add chopped celery, bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, pimento, soup, peas, Ro-Tel and chopped chicken.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken
directions: Place breasts in shallow baking dish.
Mix together dressing mix and soup; pour soup mixture over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until chicken is tender.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine
sugar,
syrup and water and cook over low heat until sugar
is
dissolved.
Cook
until mixture dropped into very
cold water
forms
a
firm ball.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a
thin	stream into
egg	whites.
Add
vanilla.	Beat until mixture
holds
its shape and may become too stiff for mixer. Add nuts.
Drop mixture from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: krumkake
directions: Beat eggs until very light. Add sugar, melted butter, cream and vanilla. Add flour. Place 1 teaspoon dough on Krumkake iron; bake until light brown. Roll or fold as desired.

title: irish raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar with a spoon.
Add eggs, milk and raisins (and optional caraway seed).
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix ingredients in order written.
Spread in greased, floured 11 x 17-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: bake potato soup
directions: Saute onion in melted butter for 10 minutes in a large kettle. Add flour to onions and butter and cook four to five minutes, stirring until flour is absorbed.

In a separate container, combine water, chicken bouillon, potato flakes, and seasonings. Stir until thoroughly mixed and no lumps remain. Add to onion mixture, one pint at a time. Add milk and cream, stirring until smooth and lightly thickened. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes. In a separate container, the potatoes should be covered with water, brought to boil, and simmered for 20 minutes. Combine the potatoes with the soup to complete.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 dish with bag of cookies. Combine milk and pudding mix; blend well. Combine cream cheese and condensed milk; mix smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Add to pudding mixture. Pour all mixture over cookies and bananas. Cover with remaining cookies. Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add remaining ingredients. Beat well. Put dough in a greased bowl. Let rise until doubled. Punch down and roll to a 15 x 9-inch rectangle. Mix the brown sugar, butter and cinnamon together and spread on top of the rectangle. Roll tightly; slice in 1-inch pieces. Place in 2 round 8-inch pans or 13 x 9-inch pan. Let rise. Bake in preheated 375° oven about 25 minutes. While slightly warm, ice with powdered sugar mixed with water.

title: rigatoni
directions: Make sausage and seasoning into small balls; brown.
Cook chopped pepper and onion in sausage grease.
Mix sausage balls, pepper, onion, mushrooms, pepperoni, spices, grated cheese and tomato sauce.
Add noodles to sauce in large dish; cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until well heated at 350°.

title: jim's squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Crumble 1 roll of crackers in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Place squash on crackers and then put other roll of crumbled crackers evenly over squash.
Cut butter into patties and place on top of crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste and cover with milk.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 450° until browned.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together and mix with beaters.
Add juice and beat.
Dip slices of fruit (i.e., apples, bananas and pears).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften marshmallows with pineapple.
Add coconut and nuts. Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat with rotary beater until well blended. Blend in rest of ingredients; add Cool Whip. Spoon mixture into 2 ice cube trays and freeze.

title: kraut dumplings
directions: Cook roast until tender; remove from liquid.
Reserve liquid. Cut roast up and toss with sour kraut.

title: tortillas or tacos
directions: Brown beef in small amount of oil.
Add taco seasoning and cook as package directs.
Shred lettuce, grate cheese and cut other ingredients.
Heat shells as package directs.
Let each person assemble as desired.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla until crumbly.
Press half of crumbs into a greased baking dish. Add the diced rhubarb.
Combine the sugar, cornstarch, water and 1 teaspoon vanilla and cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: honey-baked bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cut bananas in half crosswise. Brush with margarine. Arrange in a shallow dish. Combine honey and orange juice in a small bowl. Mix well and pour over bananas. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake for 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: fig bread
directions: Mix butter, figs, nuts, sugar and boiling water. Allow to cool. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Mix this cookie base well and press evenly into a greased 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: black olive champagne soup
directions: Over low heat, cook until thickened the butter, leeks and flour.
In a blender, add to the cooked mixture the bouillon, pepper, tarragon and champagne.
Blend well.
Return to pan; add the cream and olives.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients (I prefer to put milk, onion, bell pepper and chili pepper in blender for a few seconds).
Add additional milk if needed.
Bake at 450° until done and well browned on top and bottom.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Place pineapple in a bowl.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Stir to blend.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Frost cake.
This cake must be kept in the refrigerator.

title: good cereal cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients, then add oil, egg and sour milk.
Sift the flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients last.
Roll into balls on greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap each shrimp with bacon.
Place all in baking pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Cook at 475° for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp over (use more barbecue sauce if wanted). Cook for 5 minutes more.
May need to turn broiler on to finish cooking bacon.

title: poke weed-n-onions
directions: Dice poke weed and onions.
Blanch in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain.
Bread with corn meal.
Saute in oil until lightly brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and the following dressing and mix well.

title: specalacy cookies
directions: Mix oleo and flour with hands.
Add sugar, cinnamon and lemon rind.
Add eggs (beaten) and place dough in a floured dish; cover and let stand in cool place for a week.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle on hartshorn, fold and roll out several times.
Roll thin. Cut and bake on ungreased sheet at 350°.

title: neely's salad
directions: Shred in 1/2-inch strips, all lettuce.
Toss.
Add chopped tomato.
Sprinkle garlic salt on top.
Add the two dressings and Parmesan cheese.
Toss and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt over low heat the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Put cereal in a large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal and mix well.
Put powdered sugar into a large paper bag and add cereal mixture.
Shake carefully, but thoroughly.

title: smoky egg dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon; beat until smooth and chill.
At serving time, fold in crumbled bacon, reserving a little for trim.
Or omit bacon and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crisp crackers or chips.
Yield: 1 3/4 cups.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cook Jell-O and cool for 3 minutes; stir in whipped cream to dissolve in with Jell-O.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell. Slice strawberries; add remaining whipped cream to top of Jell-O. As a topping, place sliced strawberries on top of whipped cream topping.
Chill and enjoy when Jell-O is set.

title: "quickie" chocolate mousse pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust or use ready-made.
In a bowl, mix the chocolate pudding and cold milk with hand mixer for 3 minutes. Add 1 tub Cool Whip; mix until well blended.
Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips (optional) and hand mix.
Add Kahlua (optional) and mix well. Pour into pie crusts.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle tops with 1/4 cup chocolate chips (optional).
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Slice.
Serve cold.
Makes 2 pies, serving 6 to 8 each.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Cook noodles per directions on box.
Brown beef; drain and add in spaghetti sauce.
Add noodles.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for one hour, or until pepper is tender.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press in 13 x 9-inch pan and chill graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Blend confectioners sugar, eggs and margarine.
Beat 15 minutes and chill.
Spread on top of crust. Add pineapple (drained) and 4 or 5 sliced bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over this.
Add 2 or 3 more bananas.
Top with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Heat butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips until melted. Pour in Chex and stir to coat.
Place powdered sugar in a large Ziploc bag.
Add coated Chex.
Shake until coated.
Pour out on waxed paper to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna; mix all ingredients and set for a few hours or overnight.
Flavor improves while it sets.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Good for ladies' luncheon.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter together.
Sprinkle over crust, saving some for topping.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour over peanut butter mixture.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture over pudding.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and chopped onions in salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 11 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: Cream margarine until softened; gradually add sugar and cream well.
Blend in the chocolate which has been melted over hot water and slightly cooled.
Add vanilla and eggs one at a time, beating about 5 minutes with electric mixer after each addition.
Turn into pie crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Filling may be poured into 8 tart shells.

title: honey-dijon dressing
directions: In a small bowl, whisk all ingredients together until blended or combine in a blender until smooth.
Chicken broth helps replace some of the oil.
Extra virgin olive oil has a fuller, fruitier flavor then regular olive oil.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: honey orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 12 medium muffin cups.
In medium bowl, beat egg, cottage cheese, honey and butter together.
Add oats and orange peel until well blended. Gradually stir in flour and baking soda.
Divide batter among muffin cups.
Bake about 25 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: wicked irish stew
directions: Cut beef into cubes, 1 to 2-inches across.
In a pressure-cooker or a sizable pot that can be closely covered, put the water, salt, pepper, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce and beef bouillon.
Bring to boil; add meat and boil over medium-high heat until tender.
Add potatoes, onions and carrots.
Cook until tender.
Serve with buttered bread or biscuits.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In a pan, heat margarine, milk and water to 120°.
In a large bowl, mix whole wheat flour, 2 cups of all-purpose flour, salt, sugar, yeast and wheat germ.
Add warm liquid to dry ingredients. Add egg and beat 3 minutes in mixer.
Add the rest of the flour, slowly, until the mixture is not sticky.
It should be tacky.

title: mr. i's-in-the-house cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a 6 cup mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl of at least 3-quart capacity, mix together margarine and brown sugar until totally creamy.
Add 3 eggs, vanilla and maple extracts to the margarine/sugar mixture and beat it until it's fluffy.
Pour
the dry ingredients into the margarine/sugar mixture and carefully blend.
Fold in chips.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to a boil.
Pour over carrots, onions and bell pepper. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Cube French bread; arrange in pan.
Sprinkle cheese and meat over bread.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard together.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Allow casserole to sit in refrigerator overnight (at least 8 hours).
Bake the next morning at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: strip dumplings
directions: Stir buttermilk into dry ingredients; blend well. Turn out onto floured surface and knead until smooth and not sticky to the touch. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick; cut into 1/2-inch wide and 3-inch long strips. Drop into simmering soup or stewing chicken. Cover and simmer 12 minutes or until done. Makes 30 small dumplings.

title: artichoke dip(serves 12)
directions: Drain artichokes and squeeze out all juice.
Chop and add all ingredients.
Place in a shallow dish and bake until brown on top. Blot excess grease with paper towel.
Serve with king size Fritos or crackers.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Drop by the teaspoon onto greased cookie pan and bake at 350°.

title: dottie's 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up.
Stir in lemon flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
(Keeps about 2 weeks in refrigerator.)
Makes 20 servings, 338 calories.

title: artichoke-chili dip
directions: Combine the chopped artichoke hearts, chopped chili peppers, cheese and mayo.
Turn mixture into an 8-inch round baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: breakfast bread pudding(low-fat microwave)
directions: Spray micro-safe bowl with nonstick spray. Microwave 3 minutes on High. Yields 1 serving.

title: rice pie
directions: Beat all together, then add rice.
Line a 10-inch deep-dish pan with a thin crust or spray with cooking spray.
Pour in filling and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set.

title: party punch
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together.
Put on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: taco quick
directions: Line lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish with tortillas, tearing to fit if necessary.
In 10-inch omelet pan over medium heat, cook ground beef and onion, stirring occasionally, to break beef apart, until browned, about 5 minutes.
Pour off drippings. Stir in garlic and seasoning.
Spoon beef mixture onto tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs and milk until well blended.
Pour over beef and cheese.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Spread with sour cream.
Top with tomatoes, lettuce and olives.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna or chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator.
Serve over shredded lettuce and shoestring potatoes.

title: helen ray's tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except Crisco) in a bowl.
Then add 1/2 cup Crisco and blend thoroughly.
Drop teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown.
These are light and crispy.

title: wonderful sweet potatoes
directions: Mash sweet potatoes and add pineapple; mix.
Add sugar and nutmeg to taste.
Add walnuts.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Cover top with marshmallows and return to oven until light brown on top.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Peel and slice carrots.
Put potatoes and carrots in boiling water and cook until tender.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour into pan crushed pineapple with juice, then cherry pie filling, then powdered cake mix. Slice margarine into pats.
Spread over cake mix, then spread chopped nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
There is no need to check cake until it is finished.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until mixture is set, about 35 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Put altogether in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon fruit mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; reserve 3/4 cup of gelatin mixture and let stand at room temperature.
Pour remaining gelatin into blender.
Add mayonnaise, cream cheese (cut in cubes) and lemon concentrate.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch glass bowl.
Refrigerate until firm.
Arrange any kind of fruit on top. Refrigerate reserved gelatin until thick enough to coat a spoon. Spoon thickened gelatin over fruit to glaze.
Refrigerate to set.

title: baked stew
directions: In covered roaster pan, place ingredients in the order given. Cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
No browning necessary.
When done, the gravy is thick and brown.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in oil in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer at least one hour.
Also good with melted cheese on top.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into small pieces, cutting off all stalk.
Add all ingredients, except mayonnaise, juice and sugar. Mix these 3 until sugar is dissolved.
Add this 1 hour before serving.
Just before serving, add bacon in.
Calories in whole salad is 1600.

title: biscuits
directions: Knead with hands until well blended together.
Sprinkle flour on tabletop.
Roll out dough and cut dough with cutter.
Place biscuits on greased pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: christmas cake
directions: Blend the softened cream cheese, oleo, sugar and vanilla; add eggs 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Add 2 cups flour with baking powder added.
Combine cherries and nuts with 1/4 cup flour and fold into batter.
Grease a tube pan; sprinkle the finely chopped nuts and pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan and remove.

title: roast supreme
directions: Place roast in baking dish. Add soup mix and mushroom soup. Cook in 350° oven for 4 hours or until done. Add 1/2 cup of water for consistency.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Beat in sugar, salt, nutmeg, flour, vanilla and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook about 25 minutes.

title: filled turkey breast roll
directions: Spread thin layer of softened cream cheese on each slice of smoked turkey breast.
Roll up.
Cut in half and secure with toothpick.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and onions and grate into bowl.
Beat eggs; add to potato-onion mixture.
Add salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture onto hot greased skillet.
Fry on both sides until browned.
Can be served plain, with sour cream or applesauce.

title: chewy ginger cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add flour, soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill.
Roll in balls, dip top side in sugar and sprinkle with 2 to 3 drops of water.
Set balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook as directed on package until al dente; drain.
Saut onions in margarine.
Thoroughly mix onions and remaining ingredients with spaghetti in a large bowl. Put in a baking dish (13 x 9).
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven until bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: nibble
directions: Mix all together and serve in bowl.

title: lil's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain and cool.
Peel and chop into cubes. Add onions, celery and eggs.
Add salt and pepper, then mayonnaise. Mix together and add pickle relish.
May add more mayonnaise, salt and pepper to your taste.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream soft butter, sugar and then eggs and water.
Put salt and baking powder in 1 cup flour and add to ingredients.
Work in flour until it is consistency to roll and cut or pinch off and roll with hands into small balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 350°.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: stuffed chicken roll-ups
directions: Make stuffing as per directions on bag.
Add raisins to stuffing mixture.
Place stuffing in center of each chicken cutlet and roll up.
Fasten with toothpick or lay seam-side down in baking dish.
Heat mushroom soup and wine until well mixed.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Sauce is wonderful over rice or mashed potatoes as a side dish.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter, and sugar.
Add flour, salt, soda, buttermilk and eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and mix well. Spray a Bundt pan with a nonstick spray.
Pour batter into pan and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until tested done in center.

title: nuns salad
directions: In a large bowl mix chicken, scallions, potatoes, raisins and half of the grapes.
Add olives, salt and pepper and apple.
Toss with mayonnaise and sour cream; mix well.
Arrange on a platter placing remaining grapes in a decorative manner on top.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in small sauce pan.
Add brown sugar and garlic powder.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Wrap 4-5 green beans into bundles with bacon slice and secure with toothpick.
Place roll-ups in 9x13 dish.
Pour butter mix over green beans.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a pan and boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add 3 cups of 3 Minute oatmeal and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Mix well and drop on waxed paper.
Makes about 20 medium cookies.

title: potluck black-eyed peas
directions: Saute bacon with celery, green pepper and onion. Add tomatoes and peas. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve in soup bowls. Accompany with jalapeno cornbread. Serves 6 to 8.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in processor or blender.
Whirl until smooth and creamy.
Keeps up to 5 days refrigerated.
Makes 1 cup.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Bring juice from pineapple and beets to a boil. Add jello and sugar. Stir until dissolved. Add other ingredients.
Chill to set.

title: beef over noodles
directions: Combine.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken salad puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, heat water and margarine to rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat; beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Cut meat 3/16 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Soak 24 hours in a crisper or a stainless steel bowl in the refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Use toothpicks to hang from oven racks.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in the next 3 ingredients, then stir in the last 2 ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; sprinkle with salt and add water to cover.
Top with ice and let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and rinse vegetables.

title: good southern corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil. Stir until smooth. Add 1/2 of this oil to the mixture. Place remaining oil in pan which bread is to be cooked. Pour the mixture on top of remaining oil in pan. Cook in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked cheese loaf
directions: Mix flour into sugar and combine last six ingredients, blending well.
Cook in double boiler over medium heat until fairly thick.
Add cheese, pimentos and cracker crumbs.
Cook in well-greased dish 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana yellowtail
directions: Dredge fillets with flour and place in buttered baking pan. Mix butter and wine together and pour over fish.
Place bananas on top of fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Baste.
Brush each banana slice with honey and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: best ever cheese biscuits
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Put in muffin tins or drop on cookie sheet (1 large tablespoon). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When done, drizzle with melted butter.

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave)
directions: Layer potatoes and onions, sprinkling flour, salt, pepper and parsley between the layers along with dabs of butter until you have used all the potatoes and onions.
(Slice what you think your family will eat.)
Then pour milk over entire top, enough to cover the bottom layer.
Use any size casserole dish that is microwave-safe.
Microwave on High about 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Cover with wax paper.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add bananas, baking soda and flour.
Mix well for 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in batter in greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown on the top.

title: ruby chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in dish to be baked in with sauce made from cranberry sauce, onion soup and Russian salad dressing (make 1 day ahead).
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake, covered at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix 1/3 teaspoon cinnamon with 1/4 cup sugar and mix with pie filling.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with 1/2 cup sugar that has been mixed with flour and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of pie filling; bake in 400° oven 40 minutes or until top is golden brown. Cherry pie filling may also be used in place of the apple pie filling.

title: hard-boiled egg cookies(great way to use easter eggs.)
directions: Cream the butter.
Separately, press egg yolk through a sieve; they will appear grated.
Cream egg yolks and sugar into the butter.
Add sifted flour and flavoring.
Put through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Add sugar to peaches; let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups. Combine pudding, gelatin and measured liquid in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until full boil.
Pour into bowl and chill well.
Fold whipped topping into pudding mix, then add peaches.
Chill for 2 hours before cutting after placing in pie shell.
Garnish with whipped topping and additional fresh peach slices.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix melted margarine and eggs.
Add brown sugar, flour, vanilla and walnuts.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brownies will be soft.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes (slice thick).
Parboil until barely tender.
Drain potatoes and save the water.
Put margarine in bottom of baking pan or dish.
Layer the ingredients as follows:
potatoes, cracker crumbs, cheese slices and a mixture of the soups diluted with the potato water and milk (have this mixture warm).

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Layer ingredients in same order in pan or glass dish that has been greased with butter.
Do not drain anything.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Combine cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes, garlic, cumin and chili powder; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce and chopped tomatoes.
Add Fritos, ground meat, onions and green pepper.
Pour cheese over lettuce and meat mixture just before serving and toss.

title: blueberry gems
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg whites, orange juice, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spray 1 3/4-inch muffin cups* with nonstick spray coating.
Fill muffin cups half full.
Bake in a 400° oven about 17 minutes or until golden.
Cool slightly before serving.
Makes 36 muffins.

title: poppy cock
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally for 10 to 15 minutes until sauce is a light caramel color and reaches a hard-ball stage (250° to 258° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from stove; add vanilla.

title: "hardee's" biscuits
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cut Crisco into flour. Add milk.
Roll out onto floured surface and cut biscuits out. Let rise in a warm place for approximately 15 minutes.
Top with butter and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: likeable bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight. Serves 10 to 12.

title: granny jones' sunshine pickles
directions: Mix the vinegar, salt and sugar well.
Pack cucumbers in jars. Add large hunk of dill, garlic bud and red pepper (optional). Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers.
Seal and set in sun for 7 days.
Wait 2 weeks before opening after you bring in out of sun. (Put in a place that they can get sun all day.)

title: chocolate-zucchini muffins
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and 1/2 cup sour milk.
Beat well with a mixer.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well with mixer. Stir in diced zucchini.
Spoon batter into lined muffin cups. Sprinkle tops with chocolate chips.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean and dry.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, dry ranch dressing and mayo until creamy.
Spread onto baked crescent rolls. top with broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, tomatoes and cheese.

title: budget meatballs
directions: Shape into balls.
Brown in shortening with 1 small garlic clove (minced) in a large skillet.
Blend in the rest of the can of soup.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover; simmer for about 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: rice chile verde
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sour cream and green chilies. Salt to taste.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole layer all ingredients starting with rice, then a layer of sour cream and Jack cheese strips.
End with layer of rice.
Bake approximately 25 minutes. Sprinkle top with grated cheese and bake 5 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bone.
Place in bottom of long casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream and melted butter.
Pour over chicken.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake slowly at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: supper in a pot
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ice cream sundae pie
directions: Stir together peanut butter and corn syrup in bowl.
Add cereal and stir until coated.
Press into 9-inch pie plate. Spoon ice cream into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Top with chocolate syrup and chopped nuts.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand. Cream brown sugar, sugar and butter. Add eggs and dry ingredients. Mix in oats (mixture will be thin). Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 30 minutes. Spread with topping while hot.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix ingredients together in medium size pan and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Pour into prebaked pie shells.

title: best two-egg cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar; cream thoroughly (12 to 15 minutes) at medium speed on mixer.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Bake in 2 paper-lined 9-inch round cake pans at 375° for about 23 minutes. Frost as desired.

title: chocolate brittle candy
