directions: Line jelly roll pan with heavy-duty tinfoil.
Line foil with crackers, break into pieces, if necessary, to cover entire pan. Melt the butter and sugar together until boiling.
After mixture comes to a full boil, turn off heat and let stand for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour butter and sugar mixture over crackers and bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread chocolate chips over crackers while still hot.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight and break into pieces in the morning.

title: my mother's white chocolate cake
directions: Combine white chocolate and boiling water.
Let cool.
Beat sugar and butter together; add egg yolks.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture, buttermilk and chocolate a little bit at a time.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine
eggs, salt and milk.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough. Roll very thin on floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes. Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick; spread out and let dry 2 hours. Drop into
chicken	or beef broth and cook until tender.

title: pretzel strawberry
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar together and remove from heat. Blend in pretzels and spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch glass pan. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in preheated 350° oven. Cool and set aside.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; add water slowly, stirring until smooth.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Boil together to 235° or until syrup makes a soft ball tried in water.
Remove from heat at once.
Cool slightly; add milk, stirring.
Add vanilla and salt. For ice cream.

title: saucepan scotchies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In saucepan, melt butter; remove from heat.
Add sugar and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add nuts; stir lightly to combine.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken with a little celery.
Do not add salt.
Cook noodles; no salt.
Place the noodles in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Break chicken in pieces and place on top of noodles.
Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise and spread over the chicken.
Crush crackers; melt cheese and mix with crackers, then spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender.
Brown pork and beef.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add cabbage, rice, cream of mushroom soup and a little water.
Add 2 tablespoons of barbecue sauce.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Add the salt and pepper to the flour and roll the chicken pieces in the seasoned flour.
Heat the olive oil in a heavy pan with the garlic and when hot, add the chicken pieces.
Brown the chicken over a medium-high heat and when well browned on both sides, add the white wine and the vinegar.
Add the rosemary, sweet basil, thyme, oregano and chopped parsley.
Mix in well and turn heat to low.
Add the chopped anchovies and 3 or 4 more tablespoons white wine.
Mix in well; cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until the chicken is tender and the sauce is thick and rich. Serves 4.

title: sausage-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove the sausage meat from the casings (should be crumbled as small as you can get it) and saut until the meat is cooked thoroughly.
Drain the grease form the meat by putting it in a strainer and setting it aside.
Wipe excess grease out of the pan. Add the olive oil and saut the garlic and onions over low heat until the onions are transparent (about 20 minutes).
As the onions and garlic are cooking, melt the butter or margarine over low heat. With a whisk, add the flour a little at a time until it becomes a roux (it will be thick and pasty, but smooth).
Be careful not to scorch.

Still using the whisk, very slowly add the milk to the roux a little at a time until you have a thick gravy-like liquid. Please not, roux's can be difficult and are different every time you make them.
You may not need all the flour or milk, but you may need more.
Use your best judgment.
Add the nutmeg, salt and pepper.
This is called bchamel sauce.
Put the sausage into a bowl Add the onions, garlic, olives and parsley.
Add enough of the bchamel sauce to bind the meat and other ingredients.
You may not need all the bchamel sauce.

title: potato sticks
directions: Let potatoes cool. Add cheese, Take one spoonful and roll until it is 5 or 6-inches long.
Dip into beaten egg. Fry in hot oil until brown, 5 to 7 minutes. Serves 4.

title: "tastee treat"
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and
place in a large measuring cup. Add the exact amount of water as the ingredients in the measuring cup. Brown the ground beef and onion.
Add all ingredients together and simmer 2 hours.
Serve hot on buns.

title: red cabbage with chestnuts
directions: Put the shredded cabbage in a bowl with the vinegar; cover it with boiling water and let it stand for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare the chestnuts and set them to simmer until tender with the white wine, sugar, seedless raisins and 1/2 cup of water.
After 20 minutes add the apple and continue cooking for 10 minutes. While the chestnuts are simmering, melt the butter in a skillet; add the cabbage and salt.
let the cabbage cook ten minutes, browning slightly, then stir in the flour and turn it all into the chestnut mixture.
When all is well blended, the dish is ready to serve.

title: hamburg soup
directions: In a 4 quart saucepan or dutch oven, saute Onions, add Beef and brown.
When beef has browned, drain in a mesh strainer and rinse with warm tap water to remove excess fat.
Return beef to saucepan. Stir in remaining ingredients except for the Frozen Vegetables. Bring to a boil, reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add Frozen Vegetables; cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Additional water may be added if soup becomes too thick upon standing.
Makes eight one cup servings.

title: quick red beans and rice
directions: Slice the sausage.
Brown sausage with onion.
Season to taste with red pepper.
Mix with beans.
Bring to a good boil and then simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: best ever onion soup
directions: Preheat broiler. Saut onions in butter until soft and translucent. Lightly stir in flour. Heat beef and chicken broth. Add onions, salt and pepper to the hot broth; cover. Simmer 20 minutes. Ladle soup into six ovenproof soup bowls. Place a round of bread on top of broth. Sprinkle bread with combined cheeses. Place soup bowls on a cookie sheet and broil until cheese bubbles.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Mix flour with eggs. Add butter. Stir in sugar and salt. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Fry on greased griddle about 1 minute on each side.
If batter is thin, the pancakes will be thin.

title: basic creole sauce
directions: Empty tomatoes in large heavy pan and crush by hand.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for a couple of hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields approximately 3 gallons.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend well with electric mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare pie shell (if using pre-baked, do nothing other than thaw).
Whip cream cheese and sugar together until fluffy.
Slowly fold peanut butter into cream cheese and sugar mixture (see note). Melt chocolate over double boiler with butter.
Brush inside edges of pie shell with chocolate.
Let chill for 1/2 hour in refrigerator.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and rub skins with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch. Cut in halves lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp leaving 1/4 to 1/8-inch shell.
Pulp may be used for mashed potatoes or reserved for another recipe.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and salt to taste.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom and beef casserole
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add beef, onion and saute until brown.
Saute mushrooms with meat if using fresh mushrooms.
If using canned mushrooms, heat in pot on stove.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on meat.
Combine mushrooms, meat and tomato sauce/paste and simmer.
Mix together cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Place half of the noodles (cooked) on bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover with cheese mixture (all).
Then add remaining noodles.
Place meat and mushroom mixture over all.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Combine strawberries and jello.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat for 3 minutes. Pour batter evenly over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cool with whipped topping.

title: mexican pie
directions: In a large frying pan, melt the shortening.
In it, saute the onion; stir in zucchini.
Saute for 3 to 4 minutes, then add the roast, chilies, beans, corn, tomato sauce, olives and chili powder. Mix all together.
In another saucepan, stir together the cold water, cornmeal and salt and cook until thick.
Stir in 1 tablespoon of shortening.
Spread cornmeal mixture over top of meat mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and garlic.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 3 hours.
Makes about 6 quarts. (Need to use a very large Dutch oven or deep boiler.)

title: haggerty
directions: Use half of bacon fat to grease a 2-quart casserole.
Wash potatoes but do not peel. Slice very thinly.
Fill casserole with alternate layers of potatoes, onion and cheese.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Top layer of casserole should be potatoes.
Use remaining bacon fat to dot top layer of potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and microwave on High for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli lemon chicken breast
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Roll chicken breast in flour mixture until well coated.
Brown chicken breast in shortening in skillet.
When well browned, remove from skillet. Place in baking dish.
Pour 1 can broccoli soup and 1 can milk over chicken.
Place 1 thin slice lemon on back of chicken breast. Cook on low heat 8 or 10 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful into hot greased skillet.
Fry until brown.

title: basic pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 c. warm water in a 2 c. measuring cup. Let stand 5 minutes. Combine yeast mixture, 1 c. milk, sugar and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Gradually add 1 c. flour, stirring until smooth. Gradually stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough. Place

in a a well greased bowl turning to grease top. Cover and let rise until doubled in size or overnight. Turn out on floured surface. Knead, roll out and cut with 1/4 inch biscuit cutter. Dip in melted butter, fold in half and put in pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together. Beat eggs until light and add sugar, syrup and vanilla. Pour chocolate on unbaked pie shell. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Parboil (this means to put in cold water and bring to a boil, then boil for 2-3 minutes and then remove) the yams; pare and slice.
Peel and slice the apples.
Mix together the cornstarch, sugar and water.
Then add the butter and lemon juice.
Alternate layers of sliced yams and apples in a buttered casserole.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325- 350°.
(Canned yams can be used.
Parboil the apples briefly to shorten the cooking time.) Serves 6.

title: shanghai chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings in a shallow pan.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, vanilla and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add eggs to sugar mixture and beat together.
Alternately add dry ingredients and sour cream to the sugar mixture.
Roll out on floured surface and cut out cookies.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes.

title: brandy balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in extra powdered sugar. Seal in tightly closed container for at least 1 week.

title: cucumber-tomato salad(number of servings: 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Mix well. Refrigerate, covered, at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: spice muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients (except morsels) together with a spoon. Stir in morsels. Fill cupcake liner papers 2/3 full and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese with vanilla and sugar.
Cream together and spread on cooled cookie crust.
Arrange fruit as desired and brush on melted jelly for a glaze.
Serve same day or crust will soften.

title: country breakfast
directions: Fry bacon, add potatoes and fry until golden brown.
Make pockets in potatoes.
Place eggs in pockets; salt and pepper to taste. Cover.
When eggs are almost cooked, cover with cheese. Serve when cheese is melted.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease
casserole dish.
Break bread into cubes and put into casserole
dish.
Fry sausage.
Put milk, eggs, salt and mustard into
bowl;
stir.
Drain
sausage
and put on top of bread cubes.
Put
cheese on top of sausage, then egg mixture and
put into
refrigerator until morning.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat until smooth.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
On floured board, roll out dough to fit a greased 12-inch round pizza pan.
Press dough against bottom and sides of pan.
Roll down edges and pinch seams together to form a crust.
Top with sausage and hash browns.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and milk together; spoon over pizza.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blondies
directions: Light oven, get utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toys from table.
Grease pan, crack nuts and measure 2 cups of flour.
Remove Michael's hand from flour.
Wash flour off him. Re-measure flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter. Get dishpan and brush up pieces of bowl Michael knocked on floor. Answer doorbell; return to kitchen.
Remove Michael's hand from bowl; wash Michael.
Answer phone.
Look for Michael.
Grease another pan.
Answer phone.
Return to kitchen and find Michael. Remove hammer from bowl.
Take up grease and find layer of nutshells in it.
Head for Michael who flees, knocking bowl off table.
Wash kitchen floor, table, walls and dishes.
Call bakery and order cake.
Lie down!

title: mad hatter cookies(no baking)
directions: Blend oats, coconut, cocoa, vanilla and salt in a large bowl. In large, heavy saucepan over medium heat, blend shortening, sugar and milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 1/2 minutes without stirring. If necessary, raise pan slightly from heat to avoid scorching. Stir in oat mixture. Remove from heat and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto nonstick cookie sheets or plates. Allow to set. Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry bars
directions: In a bowl combine cake mix, 1 cup of oats and 6 tablespoons butter or margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
With remaining crumbs, add egg and mix well.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread pie filling over crust. To reserved crumbs add remaining butter or margarine, oats, nuts and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bars.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in small cubes.
Boil potatoes and onion in salt water until about half done.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Add the milk and bring to a boil, then add butter and salt to suit taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water until dissolved.
Add drained pineapple and slightly thawed strawberries.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish or oiled mold.

title: chicken pepper mac
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Stir in chicken, sour cream and peppers.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: quickie pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers very thin. Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, and celery seed. Mix well. Pour mixture over cucumbers. Cover and refrigerate for 5 days. Stir mixture twice a day.

title: veal paprika
directions: Brown garlic and onion, lightly, in butter.
Add veal and brown together.
Add water and simmer for 45 minutes or until veal is tender.
Add sour cream, salt, pepper and paprika.
Simmer for 10 minutes longer.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese and stir in salsa and onion.
Spread over tortilla.
Roll tortilla like a jelly roll.
Repeat with all tortillas.
Wrap in plastic and put in refrigerator for two hours until chilled.
Remove and slice in approximately 1/2 inch slices.

title: susan's butterscotch crunch squares
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Pat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir while warm to crumble; cool.
Spread half of the crumbs in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drizzle about 1/2 of the topping over crumbs in pan.
Stir ice cream to soften; spoon carefully into pan. Drizzle with remaining topping; sprinkle on remaining crumbs. Freeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans.
In large mixer bowl, with mixer on low speed, beat first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts. Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool. Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: cucumber soup (hot or cold)
directions: Saute onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in warm water and add all remaining veggies.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.
Run through blender to puree.

title: banana salad
directions: Boil sugar and water together; thicken with cornstarch (you'll want to add a little water before adding to first mixture). Combine juice of 1/2 lemon, a pinch of salt and egg yolks; add to first mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from stove and cool. Add butter.
Combine in layers sauce, bananas, peanuts, etc., until serving dish of your choice is full.

title: pepper sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender.
Process for a few seconds (either chop or puree).

title: magic bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into a well-greased 9-inch square glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: baked chicken
directions: Soak skinned chicken breasts in salt water for 30 minutes; pat dry.
Pat sour cream on both sides and roll in crushed crackers. Melt the margarine in baking dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Cook 1 hour covered with foil at 350°; uncover and cook until done as desired.

title: ground beef and potato roll
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pat onto 14 x 18-inch rectangle of waxed paper.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over meat.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Chill several hours.
Slice into 6 servings.
Bake on rack of broiler pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pimiento cheese dip
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Remove top and add cheese cubes.
Process and blend until smooth and creamy.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: english apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pork tenderloin with raspberry sauce
directions: Lightly sprinkle medallions with pepper.
Heat butter in heavy skillet over medium-high heat; brown quickly in butter, turning once, 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Do not overcook.
Combine remaining ingredients except fruits in small saucepan and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve medallions garnished with sauce and fruits.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium saucepan, combine preserves, dressing, bouillon and onion.
Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Fry in small amount of oil until golden brown.
Drain.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Spoon sauce evenly over chops.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles according to package directions; drain. In crock-pot, mix milk and eggs, cheese and melted margarine.
Add noodles.
Cook on low heat for 4 hours, or up to 8 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, sugar, margarine and shortening.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease and add taco seasoning mix. Set aside. Let cool down. Shred lettuce. Add tomatoes and chopped up onions, stalk and all. Crumble chips on top of salad. When ready to serve, mix up with Catalina dressing (whole bottle). You can serve sour cream and taco sauce to taste.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in saltwater until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix onions, sliced thin, with carrots.
In blender, mix until smooth, the soup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, sugar, mustard, oil, salt and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: beef and tater tot casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion until done.
Drain off the grease.
Stir in soup, milk and chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir over medium heat until well mixed and hot.
Pour into baking dish.
Put a solid layer of Tater Tots over meat mixture.

title: quick pineapple dessert
directions: Put pineapple in a bowl. Add other ingredients and let stand at room temperature. Stir occasionally. Serve.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all together well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Cook all ingredients but sugar until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugar.
Pour on cake.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind cabbage, onions and peppers.
Drain the green juice of the tomatoes and green peppers.
Put all together in kettle; put spices in a cloth bag.
Mix all together; just cover with vinegar, then add sugar to taste, salt and hot peppers (about 3 or 4 pods). Cook, stirring frequently, about 20 minutes.

title: hungarian cabbage salad
directions: Clean and shred vegetables.
Toss with dressing.
Cover and let stand a few hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12. It will stay about 8 days in Tupperware bowl in refrigerator.

title: sweet-and-sour ham(good source of protein, thiamin and niacin)
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in ham, green pepper, salt, pepper, pineapple chunks and reserved pineapple juice.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until green pepper is crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and cold water.
Gradually stir into ham mixture.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: grandma tiemann's banana bread
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour 3 baby loaf pans.

title: basic bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in a skillet over moderate heat 5 minutes until pale golden.
Mix with remaining ingredients, tossing with 2 forks.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread mix and cool.
Break into pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in pan, pinto beans, bacon, celery, pepper, tomatoes, onions and pickles.
Mix mayonnaise with sweet pickle juice and pour over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, radishes, green pepper, onions, cucumber, tomatoes, etc.

title: after-school pizza
directions: Place tortilla on a baking sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Turn tortilla.
Spread tomato sauce evenly over tortilla, leaving a 1/2-inch border around edge. Sprinkle with onion, oregano and cheeses.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until golden.
Cut into 4 wedges.

title: "death by chocolate"
directions: Mix and bake the brownies according to directions in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Let cool.

title: banana-nut doughnuts
directions: Beat bananas, egg whites, oil and brown sugar until smooth. Add flours, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Mix until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Scoop heaping tablespoon of dough onto sprayed cookie sheet.
use butter knife sprayed with Pam to round out a hole in the middle of each one.
Sprinkle with sugar and walnuts.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 10 minutes until golden. Eight ounces of pumpkin can be substituted for bananas.

title: mom's chicken and rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 14 pan with butter or margarine.
Add onion soup.
Use same package to put into pan 1 package of water (pouring over onion soup).	Then put into pan rice and smooth out. Put into pan 1 whole cut up chicken.
Take cream of chicken soup and mix with same can full of water.
Pour over chicken.
Then put into pan cream of mushroom soup and just spoon over chicken.
Be sure to salt and pepper your chicken first.
Do not add water to cream of mushroom soup.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. To double recipe do rice and chicken and mushroom soup.

title: hummus(lebanese)
directions: Add garlic to chickpeas.
Blend well.
Ingredients may be cut in half.
Use mixer to blend all ingredients.
Serve with pita bread or crackers.

title: cheese nibblers
directions: Microwave 50% power for 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients and spread on assorted crackers.
Place 10 to 12 crackers on serving plate.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: orange drops
directions: Chop orange slices and pecans very fine.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on a lightly greased pan or pour mixture into pan between 1/4 and 1/2 inch thick.
If not dropped, cut into squares while warm.
Bake at 350° until light tan.

title: shrimp lovers chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large pan until tender.
Add picante sauce, tomato sauce, broth and seasonings; boil.
Stir in yellow squash; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and zucchini.
Cover and continue to simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until shrimp is cooked and vegetables are tender.
Ladle into bowls. Add additional picante sauce.
Serves 5.

title: christmas homemade ice pops
directions: Get into car. Turn the key and drive to the nearest bakery. After carefully looking over all the desserts, make the hard decision of which one you want. After the selection is made, pay for the dessert and get back into the car for the ride home.
To make everyone believe that you made this, mess up the icing, or if cookies, put into microwave or oven for a few seconds.
Pies can be done the same way.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Add onion and pepper mixture.
Top with 1 carton sour cream, mixed with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, baking in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with fork.

title: sweet potato-carrot puff
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown. Beat together sweet potatoes and carrots until smooth.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs, salt, nutmeg and pepper; beat until fluffy. Turn into a 10-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Or cover and chill.
Uncover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Garnish with apple slices, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water in a covered saucepan until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and mash potatoes. Save cooking liquid and add enough milk to make 3 cups of liquid. Slowly stir liquid into potatoes, adding fat and seasonings. Simmer a few minutes to blend flavors.
Garnish with paprika or parsley and serve.

title: sauce for grilled chicken
directions: Mix together and heat until oleo is melted.
When chicken is partly done, sprinkle on after every time you turn the meat.

title: italian zucchini in tomato sauce
directions: Saute cut up zucchini and onions.
Add Italian seasoning and also garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Saute for approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Place fresh Parmesan cheese in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in zucchini and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle more Parmesan cheese on top of zucchini.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and place all ingredients in baking dish.

title: ice cream funwiches
directions: You will also need cookie cutters, any shape.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook until tender broccoli and onion.
Drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; add milk and cook until thickened.
Add chicken broth and celery soup.
Add broccoli and cook.
Add cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: orange fluffy salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Mix with hot water. Cook until thick and bubbly. Stir constantly as it burns easily. Let cool completely. Then fold in whipped topping and mandarin oranges. Chill until set.

title: walnut bourbon balls(do not bake)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add syrup, bourbon or rum and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in powdered sugar. Makes about 50.
Do not bake.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Roll into walnut size balls.
Put toothpicks in each one for dipping into chocolate.
Chill overnight.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler. Dip each ball into melted chocolate mixture and put onto waxed paper until cool.
Yields about 200 candy balls.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Cook over moderate heat sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese, pepper and onion.
Mix adding mayo until it becomes a spreadable consistency.
Serve on bread.
Can be cut up into quarters for an appetizer tray.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, green onions and mayonnaise and a handful of finely chopped pecans.
Form into a ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans to cover outside.
Wrap in waxed paper. Chill.
Serve on crackers.
Cheese ball can be easily reshaped for another use and look freshly made.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Clean
the
persimmons	and
combine
with milk, mixing well. To	the
milk-persimmon
mixture,
add
beaten eggs and sugar. Sift the flour together with the other dry ingredients and gradually
add
to the liquid; stir in melted shortening. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cut into
squares
and	serve with cream or hard sauce.
Very good served warm.

title: crab spread
directions: Shred imitation crab meat in blender or food processor. Soften cream cheese and mix remaining ingredients until smooth. Chill.
Makes 48 ounces.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, flour and water in double boiler.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Keep stirring.
Just before removing from burner, add butter and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Cool and add whipped cream topping.

title: braunschweiger bites
directions: Spread cocktail bread with Miracle Whip, a slice of onion, braunschweiger and top with shredded cheese.
Broil (or bake in a hot oven) until cheese melts.
This is an easy appetizer that can be made ahead and refrigerated before broiling.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli medley; drain.
Place in baking dish.
Add mayonnaise; mix with Cheddar cheese and onion.
Crush Ritz crackers; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles around edges.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in liquid dressing until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: frankfurter crown casserole
directions: In skillet, cook bacon.
Remove and crumble.
Cook onions in drippings.
Stir in soup, water, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and beans.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stand up franks around edge.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs with oil until thoroughly blended.
Add sugar, vanilla, baking soda and water.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth. Fold in apples and nuts (dough will be tough).
Spread evenly into a prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cover and store at least 24 hours before eating.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: "garbage can" enchiladas
directions: Cut whole chicken in small pieces, already cooked.
Crock-pot is easiest.
Grate cheese.
Combine enchilada sauce, mushroom soup, green chilies, onion and black olives in large bowl.
Cook tortillas in oil, then roll with all ingredients.
Be sure to save a little cheese and sauce for top of enchiladas.
After all are rolled and put in a pan, put leftover cheese and sauce on top. Bake at 350° in oven just until the cheese has melted.
Also, you could substitute chicken for other meats.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham casserole
directions: Put potatoes
and
onion
in
a greased casserole dish. Put ham slices	on
top to cover potatoes.
In a saucepan melt butter. Blend
in	flour
and
1/4 teaspoon salt.	Stir.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Pour over ham and potatoes.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss together lightly.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle over the top 1 large can of Chinese fried noodles (5 ounces).
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork chops with sauteed apple
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Sprinkle chops with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cook until browned, 3 to 5 minutes per side.
Remove chops.
Keep warm.

title: sweet buttery beans
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no bake fudgies
directions: Melt oleo, then add milk and peanut butter.
Add cocoa; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour in oatmeal, nuts, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well, drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool for 1 hour.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: baked chicken breast with dried beef
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together and place in 9 x 13.
Wrap chicken with dried beef and bacon.
Place on top of soup and sour cream.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, covered.
Serve over rice.

title: beef and cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Top with cheese and biscuits.
Return to oven at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir. Do not use mixer. Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Add eggs and salad oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moist. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in a buttered casserole.

title: hot rolls
directions: Cover dough and let set overnight or about 8 hours.
Do not refrigerate.
Roll out into rolls on floured surface and place in greased muffin tins or cookie sheets.
Dough will be light and sticky.
Cover and let rise 2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 400° about 7 minutes until nicely brown.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Put cucumbers in jars.
Add alum, dill seed and garlic.
Pour in boiled salt, water and vinegar.
Seal jars.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a 6 quart pan, dice about 3 inches of potatoes, cover with water.
Add 1 stick margarine, 3 carrots & 1 onion, diced.	Cook until potatoes are tender; then add 1/2 box Velveeta cheese, cubed, 1 can corn, 1 c. frozen peas.
Cook slowly until cheese melts and serve.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits well.
Prepare Jell-O per directions on the box; chill.
Slice bananas into juice from fruit an drain. Beat ice cream or Cool Whip into slightly set Jell-O.
Fold fruit into Jell-O mixture and chill.
Can be decorated with maraschino cherries or whatever appeals to you.
You may also add marshmallows, walnuts or coconut.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Beat 1 egg until creamy.
Cream together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and the beaten egg.
Then add pumpkin, rest of sugar, other egg, flour, cinnamon and milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done (about 50 minutes).

title: orange-ginger pork chops
directions: In a skillet brown chops well over medium heat, about 10 minutes per side.
Add orange juice, cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Uncover, sprinkle chops with salt and ginger and top each with an orange slice.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes more or until chops are fork-tender.
Remove chops to an ovenproof platter and top each with sour cream.
Place under broiler about one minute.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and refrigerate several hours. Then toss chicken mixture with grapes, mayonnaise and almonds. Arrange on lettuce.

title: supreme fudge
directions: Lightly grease two 9 x 13-inch pans.
In a heavy 5-quart pan, combine margarine, sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring mixture to a full boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix well.
Now, add pecans, if desired.
Spread into prepared pans and cool at room temperature; cut into squares.

title: water chestnuts in bacon
directions: You will need round wooden toothpicks.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add Italian dressing mix until creamy.
Add to mixture thawed and drained chopped spinach.
Place in hollowed bread loaf.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: pennsylvania dutch corn chowder(salt free)
directions: Place first 7 ingredients into a soup pot. Cover and simmer 1-1/2 hours or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken, strain broth and return to the soup pot. Remove the skin and bones from the chicken, and cut the chicken into bite size pieces. Return the chicken to the broth and refrigerate overnight. Next morning discard layer of fat that formed on top. Heat broth until boiling. Add cubed potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Add corn and cook 5-7 more minutes. Serve immediately. Garnish each serving with parsley and egg.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover 20 to 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in a lightly greased baking dish; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and next 7 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Pour over the sweet potatoes. Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours. Remove dish from refrigerator.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: pizza dough
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a bowl.
Stir in sugar and oil.
Mix flour to make a dough.
Knead dough, let rest 60 minutes.
Shape into pizza.
Spread pizza sauce on dough.
Top with cheese and favorite toppings.
Bake at 400° until cheese is brown.

title: martin's margarita
directions: Fill blender 1/2 full with ice cubes.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Swirl rim of glass in coarse salt (kosher).
Pour mixture into glass.
Serve at once.
Or put all ingredients into a cocktail shaker; shake vigorously.
Serve over ice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cheeseburger 'n' fries casserole
directions: In skillet, brown the beef; drain.
Stir in soups.
Pour into 13 x 9 baking pan.
Arrange French fries on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until the fries are golden brown.

title: pork chops-fried rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring the water to boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in rice.
Cover and set aside.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings; set aside.
In bowl, combine eggs and 2 tablespoons water.
Cook eggs in 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings until set, stirring occasionally.
Cut eggs in narrow strips.
Add rice, bacon, onion and 3 tablespoons soy sauce to eggs; mix well.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Use leftover turkey (cooked), cubed.
In saucepan, combine butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in broth and milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in turkey, cooked peas, carrots, celery and onion.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Invert flattened pie crust directly on top of pie. Trim edges and flute.
Make slits in top crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured funnel pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheddar quiche
directions: Prick bottom of pie shells.
Combine cheese and flour.
Add eggs, milk, ham, pimento and seasoning.
Mix well.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife put in middle comes out clean.

title: zucchini-walnut bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately to first mixture.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Makes two loaves.

title: southwest baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse and drain beans in a colander. Place into an ovenproof casserole.
Add remaining ingredients, folding together gently so that beans don't break up.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover, stir and bake, uncovered, 30 minutes more, until hot and bubbly.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes(16 servings)
directions: Put hash browns into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Combine soup, sour cream, cheese and onions.
Gently blend into potatoes. Combine cornflakes and butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country style leg of lamb
directions: Cook leg of lamb according to size on temperature chart.
Rub lamb with salt, pepper and caraway.
Pierce holes and stuff with garlic cloves during the last hour.
Combine remaining ingredients and place around lamb while it finishes cooking.

title: oven-barbecued beef brisket
directions: Line a shallow 9 x 13-inch pan with heavy-duty foil to wrap around brisket.
Place brisket fat side up.
Pierce several places with tines of large fork.
Sprinkle with smoke, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Bring sides up and over to cover.
Make double fold (leave some air space between foil and brisket on sides and top).
Marinate in refrigerator 24 hours.
Place, still wrapped, in oven at 275°.
Bake 5 hours.
Open foil and pour barbecue sauce on top (don't pour off drippings).
Close foil and bake 1 to 2 hours longer or until fork tender.
Cut in thin slices across grain.

title: southern style scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions and layer with cheese in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour milk and melted butter over mixture and bake 1 hour at 450°.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kielbasa chowder
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and simmer until cabbage is tender, about 15 minutes.
Add 2 or 3 potatoes, sliced.
Simmer about 15 minutes more until potatoes are tender. Blend 3 tablespoons flour in 3 cups milk and stir into soup until slightly thickened.
Add 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and stir to melt.

title: (yankee) red beans and rice #1
directions: Cook sausage over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add onion, green peppers and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Drain if necessary. Add beans, tomatoes and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add milk, chicken soup, celery soup and Cheez Whiz.
Beat until smooth.
Add rice and thawed chopped broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Prepare each jello separate in 2 different bowls for chilling. In cherry jello, add all fruit and marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
Place lime jello in refrigerator to jell. When both are jelled, remove and mix both together.
Make the 2 packages of Dream Whip.
Mix in jellos and place in refrigerator to set.
May be eaten after 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Makes a nice Christmas salad dish.
Serves 1 cup portions to 10 to 12 people.

title: caramel cups
directions: Mix together.
Press into tassie pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in shallow casserole or quiche pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° until brown on top.
Serve as dip with Keebler rounds or rye deli bread.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apple juice in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Put in half of the apples.
Sift together flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix with brown sugar and cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly. Spread half of the mixture over apples.
Add the rest of the apples on top.
Cover with the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can be topped with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: summer squash skillet
directions: Mix together in large skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Combine crushed Oreo cookies and melted margarine.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over top of cookie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix pudding and spread over the top.
Refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Layer half of macaroni in greased 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle 1/3 cheese on top.
Follow with half of macaroni and 1/3 cheese (save 1/3 cheese to place on top layer).
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and top with remaining cheese.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: down home ribs
directions: In a large pot, cover ribs with water, salt and pepper.
Boil ribs over medium heat, approximately 2 hours.
Be sure meat is fork-tender and well done.
Turn ribs frequently while cooking.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Cream lard.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cream until fluffy; add egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot 400° oven about 10 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all well and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on pan about 10 to 12 minutes. Store in tight container.
Very easy to make and very good.

title: macaroni salad (1)
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water.
Dice celery, onion, and eggs. Mix all ingredients with hot macaroni.
Chill and serve.
Makes 8 cups.
Simple and delicious.

title: chocolate zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, and eggs until creamy.
Add carrots, mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and nuts, mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: great pancakes
directions: In blender, put 7-Up, egg, water, oil and Bisquick.
Blend high speed until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Use 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Makes 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: country dip
directions: Heat in crock-pot and serve hot.
Serve with taco chips or corn chips.
Can be used as a thick soup if you add a can of corn.

title: pork chops in a crock
directions: Cover pork chops with flour, garlic salt and dry mustard. Brown in oil, place in crock-pot and add soup.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, peanuts, sugar, soda and salt.
Add margarine.
Mix dry ingredients until moistened and mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Press crumb mixture in pan. Bake at 370° for 12 minutes. Combine milk and peanut butter.
Mix well. Spread over baked crumbs.
Add rest of crumb mixture with M&M's.
Press lightly. Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: You cook it.
Then you eat it.
Drink milk with it.

title: mrs. giles cookies
directions: Mix like pies with a blender, flour, butter, baking powder and baking soda.
Add sugar and mix.
Beat eggs in a bowl, add milk and vanilla and beat again.
Mix all together and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.

title: creamed spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, water chestnuts, chicken bouillon, salt and pepper.
Put in long, narrow pan.
Add dressing to butter.
Spread over top of spinach or cover with Parmesan cheese or both.
You may want to add more sour cream or cream cheese, or use just one.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef and onions in 3 tablespoons of shortening; add green pepper, salt, pepper, paprika, cayenne, whole cloves, bay leaf and chili powder.
Simmer until oil rises.
Add cans of tomatoes and tomato juice and macaroni.
Let simmer until oil rises.
Add kidney beans.
Let simmer for 1 hour and serve.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onions and poblano in butter.
Do not brown, 4-5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients except cilantro and simmer till onions are soft.
Stir in cilantro just before serving.
Serve in bowls with tender tortilla chips and cheese added to bowl at the table. Use monterrey jack or other white cheese.
Use tostitos tender white restaurant style corn chips or other thin, tender fried tortilla chips.

title: pan de polvo
directions: Pound cinnamon sticks and anise seeds between soft cloth until fine powder consistency.
Set aside 1/2 of the dry mix. Make a strong tea using some of the cinnamon/anise powder.
Let tea steep for 5 minutes.
Measure off 1 cup.
Place shortening into large bowl and work with clean hands until softened and fluffy. Add sugar, salt and baking powder, also 2 to 3 teaspoons of the dry cinnamon/anise mixture.
Work this mixture very well. Pour 1/4 cup tea in at a time, working it in each time until 1 cup of tea is incorporated.
Begin adding 2 cups flour at a time, working it in well. If mix is too hard, add 2 to 3 teaspoons water or tea. Roll or pat out onto floured surface and cut out with small cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake. Remove from oven and roll cookies in additional sugar and cinnamon/anise mixture while still hot.

title: mock chicken
directions: Blend peanut butter with a little milk.
Add to rice.
Combine ingredients.
Form patties and brown in skillet or oven in oiled pan.

title: coney sauce
directions: Combine tomato sauce, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
Brown sausage; break into small pieces with a fork.
Spoon a tablespoonful of warm tomato sauce into each bun, then a spoonful of meat.
Top with a slice of cheese.
Brown open buns in hot oven (400°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: maureen's broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain and season with Lawry's and pepper.
Make cream sauce of next 3 ingredients. Remove from heat; beat in cheese until melted.
I use enough Velveeta to give sauce some color.
You may use more or less to suit your taste.
Put broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli and add almonds.
Stir to cover all broccoli.
Cover with crushed cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cheese sauce is slightly browned.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on, then peel and dice.
Toss all ingredients, except crumbs and milk, into a well-greased casserole. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Add milk until it is filled 1/2 the way up.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles and cheese is melted.

title: picadillo
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook in oil for 10 minutes.
Add beef and cook until brown (10 to 15 minutes). Drain off excess fat.
Add sherry, tomatoes, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheddar-chili braid
directions: Prepare dough according to package directions, omitting oil and stirring Cheddar cheese and chiles into the flour-yeast mixture.
After the 5-minute rest period, cut dough in thirds on a floured surface.
Roll each third in a 14-inch rope.
Place ropes side by side on a greased baking sheet.
Starting at middle, braid to one end; flip dough over and braid to other end.
Pinch ends firmly to seal.
Cover; let rise in warm draft-free place 15 minutes.
Brush lightly with egg; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in center of preheated 375° oven 30 minutes until golden brown.
Remove to rack to cool.
Makes 16 servings.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
In another bowl, cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg and mix in milk.
Mix dry ingredients with wet ingredients.
When thoroughly mixed, fold in blueberries. Pour into baking dish.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake cools, punch holes over entire cake.
Mix pineapple and sugar; heat until sugar dissolves.
Spoon over cooled cake while mixture is hot.
Prepare pudding according to directions; spoon over cake and chill.
When chilled, spread with Cool Whip; top with coconut.

title: cleta's 7 layer salad
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch pan, layer lettuce, celery, eggs, onions, peas and bacon in order.
Mix mayo and sugar.
Spread over bacon layer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: peach and blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add orange and lemon juices and chill.
Fold in peaches and blueberries.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and refrigerate until firm.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray Pam on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts, cinnamon and dry butterscotch pudding in a pan.
Place dinner rolls in pan. Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Then pour over rolls.
Cover; let rise overnight or 4 to 5 hours.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Turn out onto another pan or plate.

title: chicken breasts with mushroom and curry(this is not hot)
directions: In a paper bag (or plastic), shake up breasts with seasoned flour.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in skillet and brown breasts on both sides.
Cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
In another skillet, add 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute onions and mushrooms over low heat.
When chicken is done, add mushrooms and onions to chicken skillet.
Add mushroom soup, hot bouillon and curry powder.
Stir until smooth over low heat.
Taste and correct seasoning.
Cook 30 minutes over low heat.
Serve over noodles or rice with peas and a citrus salad.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients and pour in a casserole dish. Top with French fried onions. Place in oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter rectangle Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup rice in baking dish.
Slice a lot of spring onions over rice.
Pour in 2 cups chicken bouillon (2 bouillon cubes in 1 cup boiling water, then add 1 cup cold water).
Lay chicken on top of rice and onions (meaty side down).
Put butter pats on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cover off; turn chicken and broil until chicken is brown.
Add about 1/4 cup water if rice is dry.

title: relleno bites
directions: Butter bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread green chili peppers on bottom of pan.
Spread cheese over chilies.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; spread over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.
Let set about 10 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares; serve hot.
Heats great in microwave.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter, salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Prepare large package of raspberry jello.
Add frozen raspberries and let set.
When set, spread sour cream on top. Prepare small package of jello.
Cover sour cream with jello.
Let set.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients and water.
Cook on low heat until stiff. Will pull away from pan when ready.
Remove from heat, cool and knead like bread.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let set for 30 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to oatmeal.
Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Mix with oatmeal.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (or until firm).

title: coconut-chocolate candy
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in order listed until mixture forms a ball.
Chill.
After chilling, roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on waxed paper beside stove.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in food processor, then blend in the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour for flavors to blend.

title: coconut cake
directions: Boil milk, sugar and coconut 10 minutes.
Punch holes using toothpick in warm cake and pour mixture over cake.
When cake is cool, cover with 6 ounces of Cool Whip and other 1/2 package of coconut.

title: onion soup
directions: Spread French bread with 1/3 of butter.
Toast until brown and set aside.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-cup Bundt pan. Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix eggs, oil, bananas, pineapple with juice and vanilla.
Mix dry and wet ingredients until well blended, but do not beat.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan, invert onto rack and cool thoroughly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
shortening.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cream
well.
Add
half
of
flour and half of milk. Beat at low
speed.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating at high speed after
each
addition.
Add
the
remainder of flour and milk.
Add baking powder.
Beat at low speed until well mixed. Bake in 3
greased, well floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or	until done.
May also be baked in a 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan or as a pound cake.

title: oriental salad
directions: Blend thoroughly and set aside.

title: spinach and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream and bouillon cube (crushed).
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and minced onion to taste.
Mix with spinach. Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: naked apple pie
directions: Beat egg in a middle size bowl, then add remainder of ingredients.
Spread it all in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: graham crackers
directions: Place crackers close together on a cookie sheet; fill sheet. Bring to a boil the sugar and margarine; pour over the crackers and sprinkle with almonds. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from tray immediately and place on wax paper.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Coat large baking dish with cooking spray or butter the dish. Layer half each of potatoes, onions and tomatoes in dish. Sprinkle with half each salt, thyme and rosemary.
Repeat layers and drizzle with olive oil or dot with margarine.
Cover and bake 35 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into a hot well-greased cast-iron skillet. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: cocoa crazy cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in your cake pan.
Mix until well blended.
With large mixing spoon, make 1 large hole in center of dry mixture in pan and 1 small hole each side of center hole.
Put the oil in the center hole and the vanilla in one small hole and the vinegar in the other one.
Mix all together, then over top pour the cold water.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can frost or serve with Cool Whip.
Very moist cake.

title: banana cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, blend honey, oil, egg and bananas with an electric mixer.
Slowly add dry ingredients until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients.
If dough gets stiff, add last of ingredients by hand; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: spinach bites
directions: Spray mini muffin pan, place pepperoni slices in bottom of pan. Drain spinach and squeeze dry, add all remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour over pepperoni slices.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: holiday crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayo, mustard, onion and seasoned salt. Fold in parsley, garlic powder and crabmeat.
Serve hot or cold with crackers.

title: calabacitas(squash)
directions: Fry
the
squash in butter with the garlic, peppers and onion. Stir
constantly and cook until tender.
Add the milk, salt, corn and cheese.
Cook 10 more minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together the day before being served.
May be doubled.

title: heavenly cherry angel food trifle
directions: Place cake cubes in large bowl.
Pour liqueur if desired.
Let stand 30 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and cream cheese; beat until blended.
Reserve 2 tablespoons whipped topping and fold remaining portion into cheese mixture.
Stir topping mixture and pecans into cake cubes; mix well.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt chocolate and margarine.
Add evaporated milk, coconut, eggs, sugar and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pate acadien
directions: *Fat pork rendered down may be substituted for the cubed lean pork (optional), 1/2 pound rind removed, cube.

title: everyday fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour and add to milk; stir.
Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour in first mixture (do not stir). Spoon in fruit with juice.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Melt margarine, put in bowl with sugar and egg yolks.
Put in flavoring.
Then stir in flour.
When good and smooth, stir in milk.
Beat egg whites; fold in mixture. Bake in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ham and eggs au gratin
directions: Cook onion in butter in skillet until tender.
Blend in flour. Cook until bubbly.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add 1 cup cheese; stir until melted.
Add 4 sliced eggs, potatoes, ham and parsley; mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Garnish with additional 2 eggs, sliced.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix well and pour over fruit in butter pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: raisin-carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots; add remaining ingredients and mix.
Use fat-free mayonnaise.

title: citrus cooler punch
directions: Mix orange drink and 7-Up in punch bowl.
Scoop in sherbet. Serves 12 to 15.

title: layered raspberry pretzel jell-o
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add raspberries. Put in greased bundt pan or Jell-O mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: vegetable stew
directions: In hot pan, add oil, garlic, mushrooms and onion; saute.
Add carrots and celery and saute lightly.
Add water, potatoes, butter beans, beef broth and tomato paste.
Bring to a boil.
Add thyme, allspice, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer until done.

title: lazy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly salt and generously pepper chicken on all sides and under the skin.
Place pieces in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish or any ovenproof dish into which they will fit snugly.
Make sure the skin is stretched to cover all the tops. Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Shut off the oven and allow to continue cooking by retaining heat for another half hour or so. They will still be warm and delicious.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop vegetables. Seed hot pepper and discard seeds. Put all in large cooker and cook, and cook, and cook! Find the consistency you want. Sterilize jars and lids. Makes 4 to 5 pints. Excellent with white beans and on hamburgers.

title: pecan "surprise" bars
directions: Mix 2/3 cup cake mix, brown sugar, Karo, vanilla and 3 eggs 1 to 2 minutes on high heat.
Set aside.
Now mix rest of the cake mix, butter and the last egg.
Mix until it becomes a crumbly dough.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Pour first mixture over baked crust.
Sprinkle with pecans and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 36 delicious pecan bars.

title: crock-pot good 'n easy stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours.
If desired, thicken gravy.
Makes 8 servings (about 3 quarts).

title: cheeseburger vegetable soup
directions: Place ground beef in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown. Drain, crumble, and set aside. Simmer carrots, celery, onion, and broth for about 10 minutes or until soft. Add rice, mixed vegetables, beef, Velveeta, cheese soup, and milk, and cook until cheese is melted. Do not boil. Add sour cream and chives just before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients for crust and bake in a spring pan at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add all liquid ingredients; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: never fail charoses *
directions: Peel, core and chop apples.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Do at least 2 days ahead.
Stir and taste each day.
Add wine and cinnamon as needed.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Cook cherries and 3/4 cup sugar until tender.
Blend flour and remaining sugar.
Add milk and butter.
Beat with mixer.
Pour cherry mixture into baking dish.
Pour batter over cherries.

title: fettuce fontinella
directions: In a saucepan, saute 2 tablespoons butter with garlic and mushrooms until soft.
Set aside.
In another saucepan melt 1/4 cup butter; stir in flour to make paste.
Slowly stir in milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in mushrooms, pepper, fontinella and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Pour over cooked fettuce.
Top with rest of grated Parmesan cheese.

title: rose's rolls
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans in bottom.
Sprinkle 2 cups coconut on top of pecans.

title: mexican cheese log
directions: Slice Velveeta cheese and lay out on wax paper.
Place another sheet of wax paper over top and roll out approximately 1/8-inch. Remove wax paper on top and spread on cream cheese.
Add onions and beef.
Roll into log, pulling away bottom layer of wax paper as you go.

title: onion tomato gravy
directions: In frying pan, saute onion.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat for 1/2 hour.
Make brown gravy as usual, then add onion-tomato mixture to it.
Stir to mix.
Serve with pork chops.

title: pink punch
directions: Float ice ring at least 1/2 hour before serving.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, salt and bananas. Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: birthday icing
directions: Boil water and sugar until syrupy 1 minute, then cool.
Beat sugar and egg.
Add syrup; beat 2 minutes.
Add Crisco and vanilla and beat until creamy.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add sugars, cocoa, apple and salt. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oats, nuts and vanilla. Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or put in pan and cut in squares. (Grease pan.)

title: microwave turkey meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. mix well. Shape into rounded flat loaf, place on microwave safe rack. Cover with plastic wrap, venting one corner. Mircowave on high for 9-11 min.
Let stand wrapped for 8 min. For regular oven. Bake at 350° for 40 min.

title: aunt lola's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and sugar and set aside.
Mix flour, salt, soda and part of oatmeal.
Set aside.
Mix eggs and vanilla and add to sugar mixture, then add flour mixture and remainder of oatmeal.
Finally, add raisins.
Drop on greased tin and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise, remove yolks and mash fine.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Refill whites.
Sprinkle with paprika and refrigerate.

title: spaghetti bread
directions: Combine in mixing bowl.
Mix on high for 3 minutes.
Knead until smooth (about 3 minutes).
Raise in bowl 2 minutes.
Divide into 2 loaves
Make like french bread.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in well-greased 9 x 13 pan.
Cut chicken into large pieces and spread over broccoli.
Cover with cheese slices over entire pan.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and spread over cheese. Sprinkle sliced water chestnuts over top.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle onion rings over top and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In large bowl, combine vinegar, Burgundy, onions, carrot, celery, allspice, cloves, salt and pepper.
Wipe meat with damp cloth.
Put meat in marinade.
Refrigerate, covered, for 3 days. Turn meat occasionally.
Remove meat; wipe dry with paper towels. Heat Dutch oven.
Add oil; heat.
Dredge meat in 2 tablespoons flour; in hot oil, brown very well on all sides.
Pour in marinade. Simmer, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat from Dutch oven.
Press liquid and vegetables through coarse sieve; skim off fat.
Measure 3 1/2 cups liquid (add water if necessary).
Return liquid to Dutch oven.
In small bowl, make paste of 1/3 cup cold water, remaining 2 tablespoons flour and the sugar.
Stir into liquid; bring to boiling, stirring.
Add the crushed gingersnaps.
Return meat to the Dutch oven; spoon gravy over it.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Remove meat to heated platter; pour on some gravy.
Serve, sliced thin, with more gravy.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer crumbs, mixed with margarine.
Beat sugar, margarine and egg whites; beat 10 minutes and layer.
Slice bananas and layer. Spread pineapple over.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and nuts.

title: chocolate cherry fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan (or 9 x 13-inch pan for cake).
In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Lucie's Chocolate Frosting.

title: spring cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 1/2 x 13-inch cake pan. Combine eggs, cake mix, oil and mandarin oranges with juice in bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer 7 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool.
Blend pudding mix and pineapple with juice and fold in whipped cream.
Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate until served.

title: peanut butter squares(like reese's peanut butter cups)
directions: Mix the sugar, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and margarine together well.
Press evenly and firmly into a buttered 9 x 11-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over hot water.
Spread over top of first mixture.
Cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Very rich.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place the apples in a 1-quart casserole. Combine orange juice, sweetener, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour over apples and toss.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash, onions and peppers, sprinkle with salt.
Let set 1 hour.
Drain. Make a syrup of sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Pour over squash, peppers and onions. Let boil a few minutes.
Pack in jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: pineapple delight pie
directions: Mix well.
Put into cold pie shell.

title: finger salad
directions: Mix marinade ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: jam cake with pineapple filling
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Crush chips in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown and drain ground beef and place over chips.
In a bowl, mix soups, tomato sauce, seasoning mix and 1/2 cup water.
Mix well and pour over ground beef.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour in small bowl to make smooth paste. Add to hot milk in saucepan, gradually stirring constantly.
Add the next 7 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange tomato slices over top.
Brown bread crumbs in bacon drippings in a skillet.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked brie with blue cheese and walnuts
directions: Slice Brie in half horizontally.
Place Blue cheese and 2 tablespoons of the walnuts over cut side of bottom half of the Brie.
Replace top half.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar. Bring to boil the margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola. Pour over dry mixture and stir well. Mix sour cream with soda; add to other mixture, then add eggs and vanilla. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°, approximately 40 minutes.

title: fran's macaroni and tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook macaroni. Mix together other ingredients together, top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 2 tbsp butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: french-style peas
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon fat, then blend in flour and seasoning.
Add cream gradually and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add peas and mushrooms and heat.
Serve over toast triangles.

title: cherry almond salad
directions: Strain cherries, but save about 2 tablespoons of cherry juice for coloring.
Mix all the ingredients.
You can slice or leave cherries whole.

title: albondigas soup
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, garlic, rice, cumin and salt and pepper.
Make into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Drop into boiling water. Add onion and all else; reduce heat, cover and let simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until rice/meat mixture is tender.
Serve hot soup garnished with chopped cilantro, accompanied with warm tortillas and/or corn bread.
A dash of Tabasco adds zest.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter to consistency of mayonnaise; add sugar gradually, while continuing to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing according to directions. Break cauliflower into florets.
Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: real hot german potato salad
directions: Chop and combine the lettuce, onions and parsley in a large bowl.
Peel and dice potatoes; cook until tender and drain.
Add to lettuce combination.
Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Add cider vinegar and heat until boiling.
Pour over potato mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well. Add vanilla wafer crumbs and flavoring; mix well.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour in well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Mix together chopped meat, eggs and mustard.
Form small meatballs (makes about 100).
Put rest of ingredients in large pot.
Heat until cranberry sauce is mixed with other ingredients. Add meatballs and cook over low flame for 40 minutes.

title: kitchen sink salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Cover and blend at low speed then increase speed and blend until thoroughly mixed. Makes about 1 quart. Refrigerate covered.

title: ham chippers
directions: Prepare pie crust, using package directions.
Spread crushed potato chips on well-floured surface.
Roll pastry over chips about 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch rounds.
Fit into about 24 muffin cups.
Prick each with fork and chill at least 15 minutes.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Rub on all sides.
Mix meat tenderizer, garlic salt, onion salt and celery salt.
(Use twice as much onion salt as each of others.)
Sprinkle on meat.
Cover with foil.
Place in fridge overnight.
When ready to bake, sprinkle with salt and pepper and a little Worcestershire sauce. Bake covered for about 5 hours at 275°.
Uncover meat.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Bake 1 hour.
Good without sauce.
Can use sauce for reheating.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
Bring to boil and simmer for approximately 1 minute the sugar, milk and 1/2 package of coconut.
Add vanilla.
Cool cake 15 minutes and then punch holes all over cake using a dinner fork.
Spoon mixture over cake.
When cake is cool, spread Cool Whip over cake and other half of 9 ounce package of coconut.
