Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal coconut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375° Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine Crisco, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in oats, coconut and 1 cup chocolate chips with spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown. Remove to cooling rack.
Cool completely.

title: chili
directions: Simmer the first six ingredients for 45 minutes; add beans. Continue to simmer for another 30 minutes.

title: grisanti's italian spinach
directions: Scoop
out
tomatoes;
salt
inside slightly and chill. Fill with chopped celery, parboiled green peppers, parsley and artichoke hearts, well mixed with mayonnaise to which a little cream has been
added.
Chill
and	serve
with
fish
or as a salad.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Mix mushrooms and cream cheese together; thin with milk and add seasonings.
Pour into casserole dish; bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with crackers or toast points.
Makes 16 servings.

title: meat casserole
directions: Put hamburger in a 2 1/2 quart casserole or 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Pour cans of soup as given over meat.
(No salt or pepper.) Cover top of casserole with Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until done in 375° oven.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Slice bananas in a bowl.
Add strained pineapple chunks and fruit cocktail or other fruit.
Add frozen strawberries.
Take 2 cups of drained fruit juice.
Mix juice with pudding.
Pour over fruit and let stand several hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: flower pot and dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip and sugar.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Combine cheese and pudding mixtures. Layer with crushed Oreos in large flower pot ending with chocolate crushed Oreo "dirt" on top.
Chill 2 hours.
Insert flowers in center of pot for presentation.
Remove flowers before serving. This is a rich pudding type cake.
Real flowers may be used by wrapping stems with foil.

title: peanut butter & cracker fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a 2 quart saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute or until a soft ball forms when a small amount is dropped into cold water. Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter, vanilla and crackers. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper, cool until set. Makes 40 to 45 pieces.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, melted chocolate, vanilla, flour and chopped nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes. Ice cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and fold in zucchini and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Mix well.
Refrigerate to get cold.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over ice.
Serves 50.

title: fettuccine alfredo with crabmeat
directions: In large saucepan, stir together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk over low heat.
Cook until smooth. Add crabmeat and cook until heated through.
Pour over cooked fettucini.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter. Puree the onion and celery with a bit of the broth in a food processor and set aside.
Simmer the tapioca with 2 cups of the broth for about 8 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place the pureed mixture and pumpkin in a large pot.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer until warm.
Add tapioca and half and half.
Cook until hot.
Add seasoning and serve.
Serves 10.

title: date loaf
directions: Cut dates.
Pour boiling water over them.
Add soda and let stand while creaming sugar and butter.
Add egg yolk, flour, salt, nuts and vanilla to sugar and butter.
Then add dates and beaten white of 1 egg.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid. Add milk to salmon liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Add to biscuit mix along with egg and lemon juice. Blend in salmon, vegetables and seasoned salt. Drop batter by spoonfuls into deep fat until golden brown on both sides. Drain on paper towels.

title: ritzy dessert pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar.
Fold in chopped nuts, finely crushed crackers and vanilla.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool; top with whipped topping when serving.
Refrigerate.
Pie is even better the second day!

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine; add water 1 can at a time. Simmer 2 hours.

title: mexican hot dogs casserole
directions: Heat the 1 tablespoon butter or oleo and cumin in nonstick skillet. Add the hot dogs and cook 3 minutes. Cook tomato and frozen corn 3 minutes. Add to hot dog mixture. Add the salsa to above mixture and heat through. Serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: greek salad
directions: In mixing bowl, toss together the torn lettuce, curly endive and onion rings; mound onto 8 individual salad plates.
Atop the greens, arrange tomatoes, Feta cheese, olives and the anchovies, if desired.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Blend cheese, mayonnaise and chili sauce. Add crab meat and mix lightly. Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce to taste. Serve with dip chips.

title: banana split cake no bake dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, softened oleo, eggs and vanilla together until fluffy.
Spread over crust; spread pineapple over sugar mixture, then arrange banana slices over pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherries, if desired.
Refrigerate.
So good you won't believe it.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix well and pack into crab shells.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in moderate 350° oven about 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: toffee candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 10 minutes or until brown, stirring constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pour into buttered pan. Cover with 6 ounce package chocolate chips.
Spread when softened and sprinkle 3/4 cup chopped nuts over the melted chocolate chips. Cook and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute celery, pepper, garlic and onion in butter.
Mix shrimp, soup, parsley, lemon juice, salt and Blue cheese.
Add all together.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with Swiss cheese and paprika.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Spread on pizza pan.
Layer shrimp sauce, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, cheese and top with black olives.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked chicken
directions: In a baking pan, place chopped onions with peels, garlic with peels, tomatoes, celery, carrots and water.
Salt and pepper chicken; place on top of ingredients in baking pan and bake for 45 to 60 minutes in 375° oven.
After 20 minutes, baste with beer. Baste every 1/2 hour.

title: roll kabob
directions: Wash ground beef and let it sit in a colander for at least one hour. Well drained ground beef is the key to successful kabobs.
Place beef in mixing bowl; add garlic, salt, ginger, cumin, and coriander powder, chat masala, some crushed red peppers, and egg.
Wash, dry, and finely chop cilantro and mint leaves.
Add to beef mixture.
Chop onions finely and spread on paper towels to dry up the moisture, also add to beef mixture. Finely chop green chilies and combine with the beef.

title: chicken croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese, chicken, mushrooms, onion and some salt and pepper in a bowl.
Then put mixture on croissant roll; then roll it up.
Baste with butter, then sprinkle Italian seasoning over it.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve covered with gravy.
Then you eat it!

title: cheese rounds - hot
directions: Mix all ingredients together, form small balls and press down slightly with a fork on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: jelly roll
directions: Bake in thin sheet pan (that has been greased and floured). Turn out on damp white cloth.
Spread with jelly and roll at once.
Trim end crust off ends.
Turn out on wax paper that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces; place in skillet.
Add a layer of hamburger patties.
Follow with a layer of sliced potatoes.
(I usually have a thick layer of potatoes; we love them!)
Add 2 or more carrots.
Top with chopped green pepper.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Turn burner up to cook bacon for 3 or 4 minutes, then turn to low.
Cover; simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mallow topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except marshmallows until well blended.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake 20 minutes or until marshmallows are lightly browned. Makes
6 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix butter, flour and broth.
Thicken, stirring constantly. Add chicken and 2 1/2 cups cooked noodles (already mixed together).
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat to soft boil stage on candy thermometer. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until thickens.
Spread in buttered platter.
As candy begins to harden, cut into bite size squares.
I use crunchy style, but it's your preference.

title: tuna swiss pie
directions: Pierce pie shell with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove.
In large bowl, toss next 3 ingredients.
Spoon into pastry.
In bowl stir together remaining ingredients.
Slowly pour over tuna mixture.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix until well blended.
Pour into lightly greased 17 x 11 3/4-inch baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while still warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Bake in an ungreased casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes, or until bubbly.
Remove from oven; cover with onion rings and bake 5 more minutes.

title: okra salad
directions: Deep fry breaded okra.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Chop the green onions and tomato; mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Serve with ham.
Marinate chicken breast and broil.
Serve as a cocktail for steamed shrimp. It sounds like a strange combination but it is really good.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix together and chill until firm.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls. Place in large baking dish. (I like to bake around 30 minutes to get grease out; remove grease.)

title: marble squares
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and 1/2 c. sugar, mixing until well blended. Blend in 1 egg. In a 1 qt. saucepan, combine water, butter and chocolate squares. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add remaining sugar and flour. Mix Well. Blend in remaining eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt.

title: jan hagel("cookies")
directions: Work all together with pastry blender, then spread on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° about 26 minutes.
Cut in bars while warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar and oil.
Mix in eggs and zucchini; add salt, flour, soda, spices and flavoring.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and pineapple.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and cocoa in a 2-quart saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Use a tablespoon to drop mix onto wax paper. Allow to cool.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken with celery, green onions, salt and pepper until tender; drain; let cool, then cut or tear chicken into small pieces.
Cook broccoli in small amount of water 10 to 15 minutes; drain and set aside.
Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise with lemon juice.
Grease a 9x13-inch casserole with butter and add a layer of broccoli, then a layer of chicken, ending with a layer of grated cheese.
Pour about 1/3 cup of chicken soup and mayonnaise mixture over this.
Repeat layers ending with remaining soup mixture, then top with bread crumbs.
Wrap pan completely with foil and place in freezer for at least 24 hours.
Allow to thaw naturally and place in cold oven.
Set oven temperature at 350 degrees and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking until bread topping is browned and casserole is bubbling.
Garnish with parsley.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Blend in egg and butter.
Mix together vanilla, milk and water; then combine with other mixture with a spoon.
Using electric mixer, beat for 5 minutes.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fake chinese pepper steak
directions: Saute all vegetables in 2 tablespoons butter until soft.
Cook steak in 2 tablespoons oil; drain and cut into bite-size chunks. Mix meat and vegetables; add broth and tomatoes.
Cook to desired thickness; serve over rice.

title: cinnamon apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar until blended. Add eggs, salt, baking soda, flour and cinnamon. Blend well. Add apples, mixing well. Place in ungreased square pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Check after 35 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, beating well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Boil 1 cup of water and 1 cup of sugar together for 3 minutes.
Pour over cake and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: mushroom pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in rice to coat grains.
Add soups and mushrooms; mix.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir occasionally during baking.
Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: biscuits and gravy
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and set aside.
In medium sauce pan, melt oleo.
Add flour.
Stir until well combined and pulls away from side.
Add milk, onion, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, celery seed and rosemary.
Continue to cook until thickened.
Add sausage.
Serve over favorite biscuit.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1 inch cubes.
Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add potatoes and cook until tender. Drain, reserving liquid.
Measure 1 cup cooking liquid, adding water if necessary, and set aside.

title: trail mix
directions: Put all ingredients in a paper bag.
Shake well and take a hike.
Serves 1.

title: chicken chestnut bake
directions: Mix together chicken, mushroom soup, chicken soup, Pet milk, pimientos, rice and water chestnuts. Pour into greased 2 qt. casserole dish. Top with corn flakes. Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to boil.
Add cucumbers and onions; boil
20 minutes.
Pack and seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Flatten butter in bottom of pan.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and milk; pour on top of butter, then pour your peaches (with syrup) on top of that, then cook at 350° until done.
Sprinkle cinnamon on lightly (optional).

title: easy baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and add sauce. Cook spaghetti according to directions on box and then drain. Spoon 2 tablespoons sauce on bottom of baking dish. Layer spaghetti, sauce and cheese. Repeat the layers. Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges (about 30 minutes). This makes a lot, so you may want to reduce the amount of ingredients.

title: yummy corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: baked squash ritz
directions: Cook squash and onion. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in a greased casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: black bean salad
directions: *You can use canned beans.
Just rinse first.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Add onion and radishes.
Mix vinegar and sugar together until dissolved.
Pour over mixture. When ready to serve, pour bacon pieces and hot drippings over mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: no sugar apple bars
directions: In saucepan, mix water, raisins, apples, shortening, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Cool.
In mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add vanilla and the cooked mixture, flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Put in a greased or sprayed cake pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and set on rack 10 minutes.
Turn out and cut into 24 bars.
Serve warm or can be frozen.

title: hot wings
directions: Wash wings.
Deep fry at 400° until crisp.
Drain well.
Melt butter and combine with hot sauce.
Pour over wings and serve.

title: party sandwiches
directions: In bowl cream the cheese until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Trim crust from bread slices and cut each slice into triangles.
Spread each piece lightly with mayonnaise.
Spread mixture over half of triangles.
Top with the other half.

title: meaty baked beans
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add beans, mustard, sugar and chili sauce. Put in 13 x 9-inch dish. Place bacon on top. Bake at 350°.

title: stack cake
directions: Mix as for biscuits, making a stiff dough.
Divide into 5 parts.
Roll into balls and keep in refrigerator.
Take out 1 ball at a time and roll into a layer to fit pan.
Bake in greased hoe cake baker if you have one. Prick with fork and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Watch, as they burn easily.
Remove from baker to cake plate.
Spread with sweetened dried apples or fresh applesauce or cooked and sweetened dried peaches.
Very old recipe.

title: 5 cup ambrosia salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: asparagus york
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese and melt.
Add other ingredients, folding lightly.
Bake in buttered casserole for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: marble pudding
directions: Fix both puddings separately as directed on package.
Slice bananas thinly.
Layer bottom of dish with wafers, vanilla pudding, bananas, wafers and chocolate pudding.
Repeat until you are out of pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with bananas.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Beat chicken to tenderize.
Dip in egg, then crumbs and place in a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn meat and continue baking 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Combine tomato sauce, oregano and sugar.
Heat just to boiling, stirring frequently.
Pour over meat.
Top with cheese.
Melt cheese in oven about 3 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water to cover.
Add salt, garlic salt, onion and bacon.
Simmer until soft, but not brown.
Drain off liquid.

title: company potatoes
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in the margarine 5 minutes.
Add pimento and flour; stir.
Add milk; stir and cook until thickened. Season with salt.
Add potatoes and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: no-bake fudge
directions: In a large pot combine milk and sugar; bring to a full boil. Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter, chips and nuts.
Stir until well mixed and stiff.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Do not cut until cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and peanut butter in bowl.
Add eggs and mix.
Add flour.
Refrigerate.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hearty winter minestrone
directions: Shape sausage into 3/4-inch balls. Cook in frying pan; stir often. Spoon off oil. Add vegetables; cook 5 minutes. Add broth, tomatoes and water; heat to boiling. Add pasta. Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes or until pasta is done.

title: savory rice casserole
directions: Wash the rice and add to buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In a heavy saucepan, mix the soups.
Add the water, pepper to taste, margarine or butter and parsley flakes.
Mix together and bring to a light boil, stirring constantly to avoid sticking to bottom of pan.
Pour over the rice mixture and stir ever so lightly.
Add the onion soup mix to top of mixture and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Watch that rice does not get uncovered, if so, add water a little at
a time to keep moist. Serve with chicken or any other meat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini boats
directions: In food processor, puree the coriander with garlic, walnuts, Parmesan and salt to taste.
With motor running, add 2/3 cup of oil in a stream and blend the pesto until it is smooth.
Transfer pesto to bowl; wrap and chill for 30 minutes.
(May be made 2 days in advance and kept chilled and covered.)

title: frozen candy bars(diabetic)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Line shallow 9 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Freeze.

title: pasta frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a pie plate.
Beat eggs in bowl. Stir in all remaining ingredients, except butter.
Pour into pie plate.
Cut up butter and place pieces all over the top of the mixture.
Bake 10 minutes.
Very gently stir mixture.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes, until knife in center comes out almost dry.
Can cut and serve immediately.

title: reese's squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
You may have to add a small amount of milk if mixture is too stiff.
Press onto cookie sheet. Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Pour over crust.
When cool, cut into squares.
Do not refrigerate.

title: pecan logs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Grease hands with shortening and gradually knead enough powdered sugar into marshmallow cream mixture until consistency is stiff.
Divide mixture into 8 portions.
Shape each into a 6-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze 1 hour.
Combine caramels and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until caramels melt and mixture is smooth.
Dip each log into mixture then roll in pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator or freezer for up to 1 month.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices to serve.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
Mix all other ingredients together and shape into loaf in glass pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Pour off all grease and top with reserved tomato sauce.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more.

title: pumpernickel bread with dip
directions: Mix Lipton onion soup mix and sour cream.
Cut a hole in the top of the loaf nearly as large as the loaf itself.
Keep the bread that was removed in one piece (or as close as possible).
Put it on a plate and fill the hole with the dip.
Place the removed bread on the side to tear off pieces and dip in onion dip.

title: karo quick chocolate fudge
directions: Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with plastic wrap.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir corn syrup and milk.
Add chocolate.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium-low heat until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla; add confectioners sugar.
With wooden spoon, beat until smooth and creamy.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Turn out onto cutting board; peel off plastic wrap.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Crust berries completely (you should have about 2 cups mashed fruit).
Measure 2 cups fruit with juices into bowl.
Thoroughly mix in sugar; let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and soda. Beat butter and sugar until creamy and add eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: spiced pineapple pick-ups
directions: Day or two ahead:
Drain syrup from pineapple; add vinegar, sugar, salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Heat 10 minutes; add pineapple. Bring to boil.
Refrigerate.
Drain pineapple and serve cold.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Blot on paper towels.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat egg whites till form soft peaks.
(Stiff, not dry.) Gradually add small amounts of sugar beating slowly till sugar is gone.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven; turn off heat. Leave in oven until it cools to room temp.
Store in airtight containers.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Press in chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Stir in taco seasonings.
Cut lettuce and tomato salad style.
Put cooled meat over lettuce and tomato. Add 1 package taco cheese.
Crunch bag of taco chips and put over top.
Add Catalina dressing just before serving; toss.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until browned, at 400°.
These may be frozen and reheated for 10 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and slightly beaten egg.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan greased only on bottom.
Blend frosting mix into cream cheese; reserve 3/4 cup.
Add eggs to mixture and spread on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with reserved mixture.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours before using.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in large bowl, dice tomatoes.
Mix hamburg, taco mix and cheese together into lettuce and tomatoes.
Crush Doritos; fold into mixture.
Pour dressing over and mix.
Do not prepare until ready to serve.

title: canned okra
directions: Cover okra with water; add salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; cook until okra changes color.
Pack in jars and cover with liquid mixture.
When opening, drain off liquid and rinse well.
Batter and fry.

title: chili beef skillet
directions: Brown meat and onions in electric skillet.
Stir in the next 6 ingredients, 3/4 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes; stir often.
Add cheese.
Cover; melt cheese.
Serves 6.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix in very large bowl in order listed.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Do not overbake; will be chewy.)

title: eggplant "turkish style"
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Heat oil in heavy frypan and saute garlic 3 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Add onion, green pepper and eggplant and cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cook slowly over low fire 20 minutes until eggplant is tender.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge tomato slices with this mixture.
Place in heavy skillet containing hot bacon drippings.
Fry slowly until brown, turning once.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Mix all together ingredients as given.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered baking dish (2-quart capacity).
Bake in preheated oven. Stir pudding when baking is half done.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
No cover.

title: stew with ginger dumplings
directions: Mix stew, chow mein vegetables, chestnuts, soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon ginger in 10-inch skillet.
Heat to boiling over medium heat.
Stir baking mix, milk and 1/4 teaspoon ginger until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by small spoonfuls into boiling stew. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Cook 10 more minutes, covered. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: betik's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Boil for 5 minutes (stir constantly).
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Let stand at room temperature.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: sugarless muffins
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, milk and mayonnaise along with Sweet 'N Low.
Stir in berries.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Fill about half full.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 8 muffins.

title: pepperoni snack
directions: Blend the pepperoni, sour cream and cream cheese in a blender. Set aside filling.
Cut each biscuit in half and bake according to directions on can.
Let cool.
Slice the biscuits and put the filling in the middle.
Serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine ground beef and sausage. Add dry mix, egg, crackers and milk. Pat loaf to desired thickness. Coat bottom of oblong pan with vegetable oil or Pam. Bake at 350° to 400° until done.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Mix in a bowl cornmeal and 2 cups water and set aside.
Bring to a boil 2 1/2 quarts water in a saucepan.
Add the cornmeal mixture.
Boil 3/4 to 1 hour.
Add salt and let boil a few minutes longer.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until slightly brown on edges or liquids are taken up.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with seafood or steaks.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Mix eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
Crumble sausage in skillet and brown.
Drain off grease.
Put bread cubes in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer sausage on bread, then layer cheese over sausage.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with bread sticks.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with tortilla and corn chips.
This keeps well in refrigerator for up to 5 days.

title: curried chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Make sauce of the flour, mayonnaise, broth, onion and curry powder.
Cook on low heat about 10 minutes.
It should be slightly thickened.
Layer other ingredients in this order:
rice, turkey, beans and chestnuts.
Pour the sauce over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients well and shape into a loaf.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices and dip in flour.
Brown slightly on both sides in a small amount of hot oil.
Place the slices in a casserole dish.
Dilute a can of mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour into skillet after all meat is removed.
(This will give the soup the flavor of the meat.)
Pour the mixture over the meat slices.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
On greased cookie sheet, line up balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 7 dozen.
Dip in honey mustard sauce (salad dressing works great!).
Can be reheated in microwave for 30 seconds.

title: dill dip mix
directions: Mix all together.
Make the day before using it.
Refrigerate.

title: cloud nine biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: drop cakes
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to batter alternately with milk.
Drop by tablespoons on cookie sheet and bake at 420° until lightly browned.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter or oleo in saucepan and add brown sugar.
Cook until blended, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly; add milk and beat until smooth.
Add xxxx sugar gradually until right consistency to spread.
May add more sugar, if needed.
Makes a very creamy caramel frosting which never gets hard as it is used.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat up pan.
Add oil to the pan.
Put in rice and stir frequently.
When rice is lightly toasted, add tomato sauce and stir.
Add 4 cups water.
Let it boil on low heat for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add garlic to rice when boiling.
When rice is done, cover and let it simmer for 20 minutes.

title: lucy's mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain and combine with cream cheese, 1/2 stick of margarine, milk, salt and pepper.
Whip until fluffy.

title: beef summer sausage
directions: Combine and form into a roll; wrap in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Puncture foil with fork all over roll.
Place on rack over pan of water and place in oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
After cooled, slice to serve on crackers, if desired.
Store in refrigerator when not eating.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for a couple of hours to let flavors mix.
Serve with cut up veggies.

title: refrigerator crescent rolls
directions: Heat milk and shortening in a saucepan until shortening melts. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle or crumble yeast into water and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, eggs and salt to mix.
Pour into yeast and mix well.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Combine salt, flour, milk, butter and pepper to make cream sauce.
Over low heat stir constantly until just ready to boil. Place diced potatoes in greased casserole alternately with cheese, ending with cheese.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake in 350° oven one hour.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix together, stirring well.
Dip and enjoy!

title: apple salad
directions: Peel and cut apples into pieces.
Add grapes and pecans.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add pineapple to apple mixture.	Bring juice, butter and sugar to boil.
Turn down heat and add lemon juice.
Mix cornstarch and cold water and add to juice mixture. When sauce thickens, remove from heat.
Cool.
Add poppy seeds and mayo.
Fold into fruit and nut mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Chop drained broccoli.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spiced lemon iced tea
directions: In 2-quart pitcher, combine all ingredients except lemon wedges; mix well.
Pour into 6 tall glasses filled with ice. Garnish with lemon wedges.
Yields:
6 (1 cup) servings.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, oil and egg in large bowl.
Mix buttermilk with baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add to brown sugar mixture alternately with flour, mixing well after each addition. Fold in apples.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan and bake.
Use greased pan.
Cooking Time: 45 to 50 minutes.
Temperature:
Pan Size:
9 x 12-inch or two 8-inch pans.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into the 2 pie shells. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Add melted chocolate to batter before baking, or cover with fruit of choice after baking.

title: cheese logs
directions: Grate all cheese and let stand until room temp. Add the rest of the ingredients, except paprika. Mix well with hands. Form in to logs about 2-inches in diameter and 6-8 inches long. Roll in paprika. Be sure to cover well. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill overnight. Slice and serve with Ritz crackers. Freezes well.

title: aunt martha's rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Put 1 cake of yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Let all ingredients cool.
Add to the mixture as much flour as it takes to make dough workable.
Let stand for 2 hours or until it rises.
Shape into rolls after punching down and let rise until doubled in size (approximately 2 hours).
Bake in 400° oven until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add water to juice to make 3 cups liquid.
Add 2 tablespoons frozen orange juice.
Add puddings; cook until thick. Cool.
Pour over combined fruit.
Fold together.
Chill overnight. Before serving, add the bananas, sliced.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Remove excess grease.
Add tomato sauce, beans (drained), water and seasoning.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 35 minutes or until mixture thickens.

title: aunt martha's pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together with the electric mixer for about 7 or 8 minutes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: joanne's pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; do not overbake.
Whip cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel mix.
Mix jello, water, berries with juice and pineapple with juice.
Let this cool and spread over the second layer.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the pineapple (juice included) in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Next, spoon the cherry filling on top and sprinkle the cake mix over this.
Spread the walnuts over all and dot top with margarine.
Do not stir any of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix all together in a bowl and pour in a pan.
Heat oven on 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turtle nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake according to box directions.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 cake pan. Set remaining batter aside.
Bake cake in oven for 18 minutes.
Melt caramels; add milk and butter.
Stir pecans into caramel mixture.
Pour caramel nut mixture on top of cake. Sprinkle with chips.
Pour rest of cake batter over top and bake in oven another 20 minutes or until cake is done.
Serve plain or frosted.
Serves 20 people.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: *banana pudding*
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until thick.
Layer your vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour pudding over all.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat until blended over medium heat all ingredients but potatoes.
Place hash browns in a 9 x 11-inch greased pan.
Pour cheese mixture over and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight chicken
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Very handy when you are expecting guests. Serve with a tossed salad for a no-fuss meal.

title: sheet fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon in bowl.
Bring butter, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven in 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Put flour in cooking bag and shake.
Layer chicken in bag. Mix orange juice and barbecue sauce together; pour over chicken. Cook at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blizzard party mix
directions: Combine cereal, peanuts, pretzels and caramels in large bowl. Microwave morsels on Medium-high power for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave additional 10 to 20 second intervals, stirring until smooth.
Pour over cereal.
Stir and spread in 9 x 13 pan coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Let stand 30 minutes until firm. Break into pieces.

title: spiced crabapples
directions: Wash and drain crabapples--do not peel.
Pierce peel with a large sterilized needle to prevend bursting.
Mix vinegar, water and sugar.
Add spice bag.
Boil until syrup coats spoon.
Add crabapples, reheat slowly to avoid bursting the skin.
Simmer until apples are tender.
Pack in hot jars.
Fill jars with boiling syrup, process 20 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: mississippi cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions; cool. Stir together salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended; set aside.
Combine tomatoes and next 3 ingredients; gently toss.
Crumble half the cornbread into a 3-quart trifle bowl or large salad bowl.
Top with half each of beans, tomato mixture, cheese, bacon, corn and dressing mixture; repeat layers.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: butter pecan spectacular
directions: Mix together; press into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely.

title: turtle candy
directions: In a deep pan, put sugar, milk and oleo. Place over moderate heat and let come to a boil. Let boil for 7 minutes; time carefully. Take off heat at once; set aside. In a large bowl, put the pecans, Marshmallow Creme and chocolate bits. Do not stir. Pour hot mixture over this and stir rapidly for 1 minute. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Makes 5 pounds. Seal in foil. Keeps well.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: patty bayliss' daddy's artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix artichokes, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic; put in ungreased ovenproof dish.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve on crackers.

title: rice with water chestnuts
directions: Put all ingredients into casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Easy!
Good with chicken or beef.

title: melt away cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and bake in greased and floured pan (17 x 11-inch) at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut candy-bar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate pieces and peanut butter.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven 375° for 15-20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Melt chocolate pieces and peanut butter over hot water.
Spread over baked cookie while warm.
Cool slightly in pan set on a rack.
Cut into bars.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla, then add cake mix, 1/3 cup at a time, until well mixed.
Cover; chill for 30 minutes, then drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent roll dough into 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine pineapple juice, rum and daiquiri mix; stir to dissolve daiquiri mix.
Carefully pour carbonated beverage down side of bowl.
Mix gently.
Float lime slices atop punch. Makes 18 five ounce servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop. Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and spoon into a greased casserole dish (small). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until very bubbly. Serve with Fritos Scoops chips.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in butter until soft.
Add flour and seasonings.
Mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add egg.
Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Add corn.
Mix well.
Turn into greased baking dish, 6 x 10 x 2-inch.
Mix bread and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of corn mixture.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top is browned.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: In medium size bowl, coarsely crush the crackers with your hands - you should have big cracker pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix well and serve immediately.
Season to taste, with salt and pepper.
Can be made ahead but add crackers last so they don't get soggy.

title: summer berry pie
directions: In large bowl mix berries.
Pour into prepared pastry shell. In medium saucepan, mix sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add water and stir until smooth.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.

title: salsa
directions: Peel tomatoes; remove cores and chop.
In an 8-quart saucepan combine all ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring often. Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes or until desired thickness.
(I simmer 2 hours.)
Prepare jars and lids as usual for canning. Pour into jars and seal.
Process in boiling water 15 minutes. Makes 6 pints.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 375° and melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the brown sugar in a large mixing bowl and pour the melted butter over it.
Cream in butter and sugar, then beat in eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder, vanilla and pecans and pour back into the already buttered pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: double nut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine cake mix, melted butter and egg in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and 1/4 cup almonds.
Shape rounded tablespoonfuls dough into balls.
Place remaining 3/4 cup almonds in shallow bowl. Press top of cookie in almonds.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheets.
Remove to cooling racks.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: lucille's dishpan kraut
directions: Chop enough cabbage to make 10 or 12 quarts of kraut.
Mix in large pan the cabbage, vinegar, salt and water.
Mix well and spoon into quart jars.
Press cabbage down.
You will have some extra juice.
Boil seals.
Amount will vary according to the size of cabbage.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use a heavy-duty mixer for this or knead well.
Pour milk over the sugar and oleo.
Add dissolved yeast.
Mix dry ingredients. Add flour mixture one cup at a time.
Put in large bowl and let rise until double.
Add one more cup of flour and store in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to use.
To use, roll out thin, cut into strips and dip strips into butter or oleo and layer into large baking pans.
Let rise again and bake at 425° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
You don't have to use all this at one time.
This will stay up to two weeks in the refrigerator. You will need about 2 sticks of melted oleo or butter to dip the strips into before layering into the pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine Bisquick, butter and milk until smooth.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish, spread chicken and vegetables evenly in the dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in a boiler.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Cover with Bisquick mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 400° until brown.

title: baked bean casserole(microwave)
directions: Place bacon on a paper towel lined paper plate.
Heat on Full power covered with paper toweling 3 minutes or until crisp.
In a deep 1 1/2-quart heat-resistant, nonmetallic casserole combine beans, onion, catsup, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Crumble bacon and sprinkle over baked bean mixture.
Heat uncovered on roast for 12 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.

title: raspberry-cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water. Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and freeze.
Dip in chocolate or almond bark.
Lay on waxed paper.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla, then add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Put into ungreased small tart pans.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
As soon as you take them from oven, press a miniature peanut butter cup in center.
Leave in pan until cooled, about 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
In saucepan over medium heat, stir in soup and cream cheese cubes. Cook until smooth.
Layer frozen potatoes and hot cream sauce, ending with sauce.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: almost zero salad dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a jar.
Shake well. Refrigerate until needed.
Serve over salad greens.
Makes 1/2 cup.
One serving of 2 tablespoons = 6 calories, 09 protein, 25 g carbohydrate, 09 fat and 31 mg. sodium.
One serving = free.

title: cinnamon-orange oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use muffin liners. In one bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Pour onto dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
Scoop by 1/4 cupfuls.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until toothpick comes out sticky, but not wet.

title: blackened redfish
directions: On sheet of wax paper or a paper plate, combine seasonings and mix thoroughly; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet, heat oil over high heat until oil begins to smoke, 3 to 4 minutes.
While oil is heating, dredge fish in paprika mixture, coating both sides evenly.
Carefully place fish in skillet and cook until bottom is charred, 2 to 3 minutes.
Using a spatula, carefully turn fish over and cook until charred and cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes longer (depending on thickness of fillet).
Transfer fish to serving platter and garnish with lemon wedges.

title: small polenta
directions: Moisten corn meal in water.
Boil water, then add salt.
Add polenta mixed with water.
So it will not lump, keep mixing until right texture.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Pour melted margarine in baking dish.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tuna crunch salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Then add cabbage and toss.
Heap in bowl and sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Stir after 1/2 hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients together. Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: sister lula mcallister's layer fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in four layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cake cool before icing.

title: slush punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until dissolved.
Cool.
Blend bananas in blender.
Add dissolved sugar water, blended bananas, mixed orange juice, lemon juice or ReaLemon, pineapple juice and water.
Mix and freeze, stirring when about half frozen.
Take from freezer; let set out short while.
Then mix half and half with 7-Up in your blender.
Serve.

title: chocolate fudge cream pie
directions: Mix 1 1/3 cups sugar, flour and cocoa in a 2-quart saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Cook and stir over low heat 5 minutes.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into the egg yolks.
Return egg-chocolate mixture into saucepan.
Cook and stir until very thick.
Take from heat.
Stir in pecans, butter or margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Cool 5 minutes.
Spread in baked shell.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: cottage cheese sausage
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then blend in peanut butter and onions with cottage cheese.
Fry in patties until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Add whole cranberry sauce.
Chill until thick.
Fold in sour cream.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate. Serves 8.

title: cookie pops
directions: Will also need 10 popsicle sticks.

title: farfalle with peas & sun dried tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in medium skillet and add onion. Saute until golden. Stir in tomatoes and garlic. Set aside. Cook bowties in boiling water 3 minutes. Add peas and cook until pasta is tender, about 8 minutes; drain. Toss oil mixture with pasta mixture until blended. Sprinkle with pepper and grated cheese.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar together. Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sift granulated sugar, 1/4 cup flour and baking powder together. Add eggs and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth. Spread over crust. Bake 25 minutes longer.
Let cool 10 minutes, then frost.

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Put 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan (slightly greased).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
In saucepan, melt caramels with milk.
Spread on crust, then put Hershey bars on caramel.
Spread the rest of oatmeal on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well.
Pour on salad and add croutons, hard-boiled eggs, bacon and sliced water chestnuts.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients thoroughly, then add dry ingredients until blended.
Pour into muffin pan and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and almonds in bowl; set aside.
Combine syrup, sugar and butter in small heavy saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
While stirring, gradually add flour/almond mixture. Drop batter by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
(No more than 6 cookies at one time as they spread.)
Bake 9 minutes. Wait 1 minute and remove from sheet. Dip one edge in melted chocolate.
Refrigerate to set.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients until fluffy. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
This is a fairly thick batter.
Pat into a greased and floured pan (oblong metal pan is best). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If using glass pan, bake at 325°. Does not need frosting.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
To prepare tea, use 2 1/2 teaspoons of dry mixture for each cup of hot water.

title: italian seashells
directions: Brown meat. Drain or wash off grease.
Put back in skillet. Add paste, seasonings and onions.
Mix well.
Layer meat mixture over sea shells, sprinkling Parmesan cheese over each layer.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: creole jambalaya(microwave)
directions: In 3-quart dish, put oil and yellow onion.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add green onions and green pepper.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add water, chicken cubes, parsley, salt, hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, Kitchen Bouquet and pepper.
Microwave on High for about 3 or 4 minutes or until water starts to boil.
Add rice and meat or seafood.
Stir and cover with lid or plastic wrap (preferably with lid) and microwave on 50% Power for 12 minutes more, covered.
Let stand about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except for potatoes.
Mix well.
Fold potatoes into cheese mixture.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mom's applesauce brownies
directions: Over low heat, melt shortening and chocolate and cool.
Blend in sugar, eggs, 1/2 cup applesauce and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nuts.
Bake in a brownie pan, 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch, 35 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake(with cream cheese frosting)
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa together in one bowl.
In another bowl, mix sugar, buttermilk, oil, eggs, vanilla, vinegar and food coloring together.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture; mix well.
Beat at low speed until well blended, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes; pour into 3 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and add juice from fruit cocktail.
Stir gently until mixed.
Add remaining ingredients except Cool Whip; stir until mixed.
Gently fold in Cool Whip and chill thoroughly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple pizza
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water over mixture gradually.
Shape into ball.
Roll pastry into 15-inch circle on floured surface.
Place on baking sheet and turn up edge.

title: fat-free muffins
directions: Spray muffin tins or loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24.
Can be reheated in microwave oven.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain well.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: coconut blender pie
directions: Grease and flour 1 (9-inch) pie pan.
Blend all ingredients in blender on high speed.
Pour into pie pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onions.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
When melted, add half and half and milk. Stir flour and water together.
Add to thicken soup.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to your taste.
Do not boil.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in blender or food processor.
Mix all ingredients and let set overnight.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put apples in buttered shallow baking dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Add water.
Mix sugars, cinnamon and allspice. Sprinkle over apples along with lemon juice, bread crumbs and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Bake about 45 minutes until apples are soft.

While still hot, spoon any excess liquid in the pan over apples and gently pat down top layer of fruit until it is moist. Serve warm or cold as a side dish or as a dessert with a dollop of sour cream or yogurt.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rancho beans
directions: Cook onions in oil.

Brown hamburger and drain. Put these into your crock-pot or a large casserole. Add other ingredients. Turn crock-pot to low and cook for at least 3 hours or more. If you are using a casserole, bake at 400° for 1/2 hour. Stir occasionally.

title: baked apples
directions: Prepare apples.
Wash and core; peel 1/3 of the way down from the top.
Place, stem side down, in a baking dish.
Boil the granulated sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Pour over the apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes, until apples are tender when pierced with a fork.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Return to oven until sugar is melted.

title: parmesan onions
directions: Cut onions in 1/2 crosswise.
Place each onion half cut side up on square of aluminum foil.
Dot each with margarine.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Wrap well.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. In another bowl, measure flour; add soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately.
Beat well after each addition. Then add bran last and beat well.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep 6 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put all ingredients together and cook until it is as thick as you want it.
Put in jars and seal.

title: strawberry ice
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 1/2 minute.
Freeze for 1/2 hour; blend again.
Freeze until firm.
Take out of freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: grandma's oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake for 20 minutes at 200°.
Stir often.

title: magic lemon pie
directions: Blend together until thickened; pour in crust.
Allow to chill; top with Cool Whip or can top with meringue before chilling.

title: cornbread dressing bread
directions: Crumble 7 or 8 fresh or cold biscuits in mixing bowl and cornbread (make fresh if possible; about as much cornbread as you do biscuits) and a few bits of chipped up onion and at least 1 teaspoon black pepper. Have your chicken broth hot and good and salty. Pour over bread mixture until you see you have enough to make it just hold together. Cut up fine boiled eggs, 4 or 5 or 6, real fine. Stir good and put in bird or around it or in an extra pan and bake a few minutes just to set. (too long will harden the eggs too much). Then take out and eat.

title: watermelon cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, gelatin, eggs, water and oil.
Beat on low speed just until moistened.
Beat on high for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire racks to cool completely.

title: rice griddle cakes
directions: Mix rice, milk, melted shortening, salt and well beaten egg; stir in flour and baking powder which have been sifted together. Mix well.
Bake on hot, slightly greased griddle, turning only once.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook until smooth.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil; stir in milk.
Add broccoli; heat to simmer.
Add cheese; stir until melted and hot. Serves 4.

title: petite caramel pecan rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, soft margarine, corn syrup and vanilla; blend well.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Separate dough into rectangles (2 triangles together).
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle mixture over each rectangle, then sprinkle about 1 tablespoon of pecans on each rectangle.
Starting at the shorter side, roll up each rectangle.
Seal edges.
Cut each roll into 4 equal slices.
Place, cut side down, on brown sugar mixture.
(Should fit 8 rolls across, 6 rolls down.)

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together by hand.
On waxed paper, roll into two balls. Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Place pork roast in crock-pot along with 1 cup water, 1 large onion (chopped) and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook overnight (minimum 8 hours).
In the morning, remove pork and discard fat and bones.
Set aside.
Reserve 1 cup of pork liquid. Discard any other liquid.
Put meat back in pot with remaining onion, chopped, and barbecue sauce.
Cook on medium 1 additional hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Place 1/2 can of noodles on bottom.
Mix soup, cooked chicken, celery, onion, almonds and milk.
Pour over noodles.
Put remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. (I usually get a baking hen or fryer and use all the meat.)

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a 4-quart saucepan over low heat melt butter.
Remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, with a wooden spoon; beat until blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Fold in chocolate.
Spread batter in pan.
Sprinkle walnuts over batter. Bake 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep in fruit jar tightly covered in cold place.
Shake well before using.

title: raspberry lemon muffins
directions: Combine eggs, cream, oil and lemon extract.
Stir in dry ingredients until moistened.
Pour in lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: angel delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mom's easy red beet pickling
directions: Boil mixture.
Add 1 jar red beets (drained) and let boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Add dry pudding and poppy seed to cake mix, then prepare according to directions on cake box.
Makes about 30 large muffins.

title: quick and easy rice pudding
directions: Mix water, milk and (beaten) egg in pot, add pinch of salt. When it starts boiling add rice, then lower flame and let it roll; not boil.
Stir every few minutes so it doesn't stick.
When you start to see more rice than milk, remove from flame.
Add 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons vanilla and yellow food coloring.
Stir until all blended.
Pour into pan.
Add cinnamon on top.
Chill.
Enjoy!

title: jarlsberg vegetable bisque
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour and cook several minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Gradually blend in broth.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Cover; simmer 8 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Blend cream and egg.
Gradually blend in several tablespoons soup.
Return to soup and cook, stirring until thickened.
Blend in cheese.
Serve.

title: tuna teriyaki
directions: In shallow medium mixing bowl (not aluminum*), combine teriyaki sauce, vinegar, lemon juice, ginger root and garlic.
Add tuna and turn to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate, turning occasionally, for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: best ever cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 2 1/4 cups flour and yeast.
Heat until margarine is melted the milk, salt and margarine.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs; beat 30 seconds with electric mixer on low speed and 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 cups flour as needed.
Turn dough on lightly floured surface.
Knead in enough remaining flour to make moderately soft dough, 3 to 5 minutes. Shape into ball.
Place in greased bowl, turning once.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double (1 hour).
Roll out; spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (can add nuts, apple, raisins or pecans if desired).
Bake until done.
Can spread with powdered sugar glaze.

title: salisbury steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, egg, Worcestershire sauce and bread crumbs together. Form into patties. Flour patties lightly and place in electric skillet on 300 to 350 degrees for 20 minutes; drain fat. Mix mushroom soup with milk. Pour over patties; simmer 10 minutes.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Mix the lemon juice, grated lemon and dill weed.
Brush half on fish.
Grill or broil.
Turn and brush other side.
Cook until fish flakes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar and then eggs. Add flour mixture. Add vanilla and then nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin with onion & peppers
directions: Marinate the tenderloin for several hours in the Teriyaki marinade, sprinkled with garlic powder and Morton Natures Seasons. Wrap up tight in heavy duty foil and put it on the grill on low. After the internal temperature reaches 170 degrees (around 30-40 minutes), open the foil so the pork can brown around 10 minutes.

title: bobby trapp's cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix all ingredients well and pour over potatoes.
Refrigerate.
When ready to bake, top with 1 1/2 cups crushed corn flakes in 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: christmas cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mix together orange juice, boiling water, melted shortening and beaten egg.
Stir into dry ingredients until just moist.
Fold in cranberries.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat
together milk, eggs, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add corn. Pour into buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour sifted with salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick and cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix
all ingredients (except chocolate chips) together. Shape into oblong pieces.
Chill.

title: "chicken lickin' good" pork chops for crock-pot
directions: Dredge chops in mixture of flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Place browned pork chops in crock-pot.
Add undiluted soup and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald 2 cups of milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch/flour, salt, cocoa and 1/4 cup milk.
Add mixture to scalded milk.
Cook and stir constantly over low heat about 15 min.
Add egg yolks adn cook for 3 min.
Remove from heat and beat in butter and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown in oven for 15 min. at 300 degrees.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain grease.
Dice Velveeta cheese and add to mixture.
Add oregano, onion salt and garlic salt.
Spread on slices of rye bread.
Place in plastic bag and freeze.
When ready to use, place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Great for parties!

title: sally lunn muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix eggs and milk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Stir just enough to dampen evenly.
Fill hot, buttered, not greased, muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve at once with butter.

title: beef brisket
directions: Combine soy sauce, beef broth, lemon juice and salt.
Pierce meat with a fork.
Place in glass pan.
Pour liquid over meat and marinate overnight.
Pour off marinade.
Wrap brisket in foil, sealing well.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Remove from oven and refrigerate overnight.
Slice when cold.

title: eight layer fiesta dip
directions: In medium skillet, prepare taco spices with ground beef and water according to package directions.
Add refried beans and heat 5 minutes.
In 1-quart bowl, spread beef and bean mixture.
Layer remaining ingredients except tortilla chips in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: spice brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in sugar and cool.
Stir in egg, flour mixture and vanilla.
Spread in a greased and floured 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Add butter, salt and pepper, crackers, egg and milk.
Pour into greased dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, except crackers.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in top of the double boiler.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop from teaspoons onto waxed paper. Makes 40 pieces.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Coat chicken with flour and cook in vegetable oil until brown. Add leeks, pepper, wine, mushrooms and water.
Cook on medium heat.
When the chicken is thoroughly cooked, add flour to thicken.
Pour over heated rice and serve.
You can add more wine to flavor, if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets, slice red onion.
Mix in bacon and cheese.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and Miracle Whip and pour over broccoli, onion and cheese.
Chill at least 4 to 6 hours.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: For crumb mixture, combine flour, nuts, margarine and brown sugar.
Spread evenly into a shallow baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the crumbs into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: mama lois' cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: fondant roses
directions: In
large
bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, corn
syrup,
peppermint extract and salt until smooth. Add confectioners
sugar
all at once with wooden spoon, then with hands
mix	until
smooth.	Turn out onto board and knead until mixture
is
well
blended	and smooth.
Tint with food color
and form
into desired shapes, such as rosebuds, calla lillies or daisies.
Store in cool place.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve immediately.
Makes 20 (4 ounce) servings.

title: molasses frosted cream cookies
directions: These cookies are much easier to handle if you mix them up and refrigerate a few hours or even overnight.
Roll out and cut in your favorite shape.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or 375° depending on your oven.

title: oven parmesan chips
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices; place on greased baking sheet in a single layer.
Mix rest of ingredients except cheese. Brush on one side of potatoes and then turn and brush other side. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until blended well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place into large shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain fat.
Mix everything together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Blend the flour, shortening, salt, nutmeg and soda as regular pie crust.
Mix liquid (egg, vinegar and cold water) and add to dry ingredients.
This makes a rather dry flaky crust.
Take small amount and roll thin; cut with bread and butter size plate.
Fill with thickened dried fruit (about 2 tablespoons).
Wet the edge of crust all around with cold water.
Press together with thumb.
Fry in oil, deep fry or just enough oil to fry on one side and then turn in skillet.
Drain on paper towels.

title: italian seasoned potatoes
directions: Melt margarine and add seasonings.
Scrub and pare potatoes. Coat potatoes with margarine and seasonings in microwave baking dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Poke holes in Saran Wrap for ventilation.
Microwave on High 10 to 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Stir once halfway through cooking time.

title: jack's pie
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Just before done, add onion and pepper.
Drain well.
Pour into casserole dish and spread evenly in bottom.
Drain corn well, cover with meat mixture.
Add mashed potatoes, spreading evenly over meat mixture.
Cover with the cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated and cheese has melted.
Serves 4.

title: german sauerkraut rolls
directions: Drain juice from kraut.
In skillet heat oil or shortening; stir in kraut.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fry about 20 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Mix flour and salt.
Add eggs and water.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic, like noodle dough.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Put tomatoes through food chopper.
Drain off water and replace with the same amount of clear water.
Scald and drain. Add the balance of ingredients.
Cook until thick and pour into sterilized jars.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Sift cake flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, orange juice and water to dry ingredients. Beat until smooth.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and cream to a boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: special soup
directions: Do not peel any of these vegetables; just wash, scrub them well and cut them coarsely.
Simmer them slowly for 2 hours, then put through food mill in small portions; scarcely any fibers should be left.
Vary the amount of water used for cooking according to taste and desired consistency.
Keep well covered in refrigerator, no longer than 2 days; warm up as much as needed each time.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Let margarine soften; cream with sugar.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cake is done, pour marshmallow cream over cake. Leave in oven until the marshmallows melt.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Add the mashed potatoes, vanilla, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix well. Sift together the flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Add to previous mixture, alternating with the milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 10-inch pan or in layers at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good with boiled white icing.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump pineapple into pan and spread evenly.
Dump in cherry pie filling and spread evenly.
Dump dry mix on top of cherry layer and spread.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Put oleo over top.
Bake for 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie crust lined pie plate in moderate or slow oven (350°) until done, about 40 minutes.
Butter and sugar can be a smaller amount if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill the salad bowl one-half full of shredded lettuce.
Add layer of celery, green peppers, purple onion, cheese and peas. Spread topping over top of salad.
Let stand 7 to 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps well for 2 to 3 days.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook hamburg and drain.
Add sauces to noodles and hamburg and mix.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a casserole dish (8 x 12-inch), a layer of Mozzarella (1 cup), then pepperoni.
Add remaining noodles and meat mixture, cheese and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and well.	Add
beaten
eggs and mix well. Cream butter and sugar
until
light
and
fluffy;
add beaten eggs. Mix well.
Sift
flour and baking powder together.	Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla
and	mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Add flour mixture to eggs and oil.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well grease muffin tins or use muffin cups. Bake in a 350 degree oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: herbed minestrone milano
directions: In a large saucepan, brown sausage and cook cabbage, onion, carrot and celery with garlic and basil until tender.
Add broth, tomatoes and zucchini.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until done, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, heat and stir occasionally.
Divide evenly.
Serves 8.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare the night before or a few hours before serving.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and cocoa.
Add milk, eggs, margarine, coffee and vanilla.
Mix all together and pour in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mediterranean pie
directions: Sprinkle eggplant with salt and pepper.
Place a paper towel between each layer of eggplant.
Put a paper towel over the eggplant and place a heavy cutting board on top for 30 minutes.

title: becky's great rice dish
directions: Cook the shallots and garlic in the oil until soft, then add 1 cup rice. Cook for 1 minute or so until brown. Add the chicken broth, 1 cup of water, salt and pepper. Cook for 18-20 minutes with a lid on. Add parsley, green onions and lemon juice and stir before serving.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato in jacket until soft.
Peel potato and mash.
Stir in sugar until mixture is stiff.
Roll out mixture like biscuit dough.
Spread peanut butter over all.
