Roll up and refrigerate until cool.
Cut into slices.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place soup, milk and water in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat.
Add broccoli, salt and pepper.
Cut cheese in small pieces and add to soup.
Heat slowly stirring often.
Cook over low heat until broccoli is tender.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: barbecue glaze
directions: Blend all ingredients in a small bowl.
Use as a glaze on ribs, hamburgers and chicken cooked on the grill. Brush on during the last half of cooking.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups glaze.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten egg, salt, water and yeast mixture. Add flour; mix well.
Put in large greased bowl; grease top of dough and cover.
Place in refrigerator.
When ready to use, take out as much dough as is needed and shape in rolls.
Put in greased pan; let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Combine bran flakes, milk, egg whites and oil; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and stir by hand until well blended.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray or use paper liners and fill tins 2/3 full of batter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Approximately 150 calories per muffin and 2 grams of fat.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: brown sauce
directions: In skillet melt butter.
Add flour, salt, pepper and beef stock.
Cook 15 minutes over very low heat or double boiler. Consomme can substitute for beef stock.
Serve with beef dishes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into muffin papers in muffin tins.
Cover with Saran and freeze.

title: chocolate nut cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, eggs and butter, then add salt, soda, vanilla, chocolate and milk.
Add flour, then walnuts.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until done.

title: pork noodles and cabbage
directions: Cook noodles according to instructions on the package.
Drain and set aside.
Save noodle-seasoning packages.
In a wok, heat 1 tablespoon of oil to medium-hot.
Brown meat and remove from wok. Heat more oil, if necessary.
Stir-fry onion slices for 2 to 3 minutes.
They should still be crisp.
Add pork, cabbage and pea pods to the onions.
Toss until cabbage warms, 2 to 5 minutes.
Add cooked noodles along with contents of season packages.
Toss to warm noodles and mix.
Remove and serve.
Soy sauce can be added when the noodles are tossed or sprinkled on each serving.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine crumbs and 1 1/2 cups dry frosting mix.
Add margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumb mixture; press remaining crumb mixture into 10-inch pie pan. In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, egg, sour cream and remaining dry frosting mix.
Blend until smooth.
Spread filling over crust. Sprinkle center with reserved crumbs.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until edges are firm.
Cool.
Chill before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
May be served with chilled cherry pie filling.

title: deacon brodie's caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic in wooden bowl and smear; repeat with anchovies. Add oil and lemon juice.
Mix. Add egg and mix.
Add cheese, mustard and vinegar.
Mix. Add romaine lettuce; toss.
Serve with croutons, cheese and pepper.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let flavors blend several hours. Serve with crackers.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Marinate tenderloin in the ingredients for 24 hours.
Turn several times.
Remove and dry.
Rub with oil.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Put roast in pan and cook.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together in a bag and shake the quartered biscuits in this mixture.
Layer these in a Bundt pan.
Bring to a boil the last 3 ingredients.
Pour over biscuits and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken, take off bone.
Cook celery, onions one hour or until done.
Cook potatoes, spaghetti until well done.
Mix chicken, celery, corn, potatoes, spaghetti, tomatoes or tomato juice, margarine, pepper & salt together and cook 30 minutes on low temperature.

title: quick potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix potatoes, cheese, soup, salad dressing, onion and pepper.
Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with combined crushed cornflakes and margarine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Beat well.
Mix in juice, rind and oatmeal.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into mixture as for pie dough.
Add currants and mix.
Add beaten eggs and milk and mix thoroughly.
Roll out on floured cloth until 1/4 inch thickness and cut with rounded glass or cookie cutter dipped in flour.
Fry in Teflon or ungreased griddle until golden brown on both sides.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Store in tight container.

title: pork roast
directions: Rub first 3 ingredients on roast.
Place on rack in shallow pan, fat side up.
Roast for 2 hours at 350°.
Combine jelly, catsup, vinegar and chili powder; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 2 minutes.
Fifteen minutes before roast is done, brush with some of the jelly mixture.
Return to oven for 15 minutes. After roast is done, mix 1/2 cup of drippings with jelly mixture. Reheat and use as gravy.

title: candy's beef boat
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Slice top off bread. Scoop out bread to form a boat.
Cut the rest of bread into bite size pieces.
Serve dip in the bread boat with bite size pieces in a side dish for dipping.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Prepare noodles as directed. Add sour cream, mushroom soup and browned hamburger. Stir until well blended. Serve.

title: whipped dessert
directions: Whip all ingredients in bowl except whip cream; stir well and fold in whip cream.
This is very easy and is delicious. (Strawberry or blueberry pie filling may be used.)

title: no-peek chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend soups; add milk and beat until smooth.
Add rice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of raw chicken over rice mixture.
Sprinkle packaged soup mixture over all.
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: strawberry-lemon swirl pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash the 2 cups strawberries.
In a small saucepan combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in the water and mashed strawberries.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in the lemon juice, margarine and the food coloring.
Cover surface with clear plastic wrap.
Cool and then chill.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separate. Chop onion and cook in oleo. Mix all together in casserole dish (salt and pepper to taste). Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: essie's rice
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine. Add 1 cup rice.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add the tomato (cut up).
Boil 2 1/2 cups water.
Add the bouillon to the water.
Add the mushrooms.
Add liquid to rice mixture. Cover and simmer until liquid is gone.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until lightly browned on top.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, the salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoons into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2 baking dish.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix well and let set for 15 minutes until grain has time to swell, then it will thicken up and not be so juicy.
Fry in a hot skillet.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine the first 11 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes, or until broccoli is tender, stirring occasionally.
Spoon a third of the broccoli mixture into container of electric blender; blend 20 seconds. Repeat until all ingredients have been blended.
Pour mixture back into Dutch oven.
Stir in milk; simmer for 20 minutes.
Garnish each serving with cheese, if desired.
Yields 7 cups.

title: chess cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix cake mix with one egg and butter. Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: *Can substitute 1 large jar caramel ice cream topping.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over spareribs.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, flour and cup of butter. Chill about 30 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Mash out into small tart pan (ungreased).
Mix other ingredients together; pour filling into each.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then bake for 10 minutes at 250°.
Place on cloth to cool.
Serves 60.

title: little smokies sauce
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients.
Add meat and simmer 5 minutes. Serve while hot.

title: crumby chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Remove skin from chicken pieces if desired. Dip in margarine.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Place in pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: In a large bowl combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour onto heated and lightly oiled griddle. Serve with syrup or honey.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place
bacon
in pie shell, then cheese.
Combine eggs, cream, salt
and
pepper.
Pour into shell.
Break butter into small pieces over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean, at 375°.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chicken creole
directions: Put flour in dry 1 1/2-quart Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat until light brown, stirring frequently.
Add onion and tomatoes; cook until onion is translucent.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, or until chicken is thoroughly cooked and green pepper is tender.
Serve over brown rice.
Makes 4 (1 1/4-cup) servings.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Simmer until heated through.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: baked crusted gouda
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unwrap crescent rolls and form rectangle, pressing perforated areas together.
Spread dough with brown mustard.
Place Gouda in center of dough and pull up sides; form around cheese until covered.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Add marinade from one jar of artichokes to frying pan.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until onion is limp, about 5 minutes. Chop both cans of artichoke hearts and add to onion mixture.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix together and baste over chicken as it cooks on the grill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Boil zucchini 10 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Cut in half. Scoop out pulp.
Mix tomatoes, pulp, onions, bread crumbs and butter.
Stuff zucchini.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: noodle charlotte(a good rosh hashanah dessert.  serves 10.)
directions: Add filling ingredients to lined pan in layers.
Cover with additional dough.
Do not pierce.
Bake two hours at 350°.
Turn out onto platter.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let it cool before adding other ingredients.
Put all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: lemon and lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello thoroughly with boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate to set.

title: pavlov's veggie treats
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fern's dip
directions: Process cheese, onion, salad dressing and jalapeno in food processor or blender until smooth.
Stir in pimiento for color.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes and uncovered for another 30 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Use coarse blade of grinder.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl; sprinkle with salt and cover with water.
Let stand 4 hours. Drain thoroughly in a colander; press out all excess liquids.
In pan, combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in drained vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in pint jars and seal. Process in boiling water bath until vegetables are done, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 5 pints.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line muffin pan with paper liners or spray pan.
In a small bowl combine 1/2 cup sugar and blueberries; set aside.

title: chicken dressing (broccoli) casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove bones and cut into small pieces.
Combine soups and broth.
Broth is obtained from the chicken when it is boiled.
Melt margarine; add to stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 crumbs (stuffing mix) in bottom of pan.
Layer 1/2 chicken and broccoli; spoon half of the soup-broth mixture over chicken.
Repeat layers. Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: open-faced tuna tempter(microwave)
directions: Combine tuna and mayo; season with celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread tuna on toast; top with tomato.
On paper plate, heat sandwiches at Medium 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Top with cheese. Heat at Medium 1 3/4 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
In large skillet, heat oil; add chicken.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally until light brown, about 3 minutes.
Add carrots, peppers and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, about 2 minutes.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in uncovered wok (or skillet) at 375°.
Add onions and celery; stir-fry 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Add garlic and pork; stir-fry until pork loses its pinkness, 2 to 3 minutes. Add next 4 ingredients; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Stir cornstarch mixture; add to wok with soy sauce; stir-fry until sauce thickens.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.
Preperation time:
10 minutes; 7 minutes to cook.

title: britain's clam chowder(makes 8 servings)
directions: Drain juice from clams and save.
Pour juice over vegetables which are in soup kettle.
Add extra water to cover vegetables. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and make into 2 layers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, water and soup.
Stir in chicken, onion, almonds and rice.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix and butter and set aside.
Cook and drain broccoli well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: e-z mini pizzas
directions: Split English muffins and toast until golden brown.
Spread pizza sauce on top of each half.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cook in microwave for 40 seconds or until cheese melts.
Eat.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter.
Pour over popped corn.
Add peanuts and candies in the kinds and amounts that you wish. Press into greased Bundt pan.

title: maple walnut cups
directions: Knead together the first 3 ingredients until well blended; divide into 16 pieces.
Press onto bottom and sides of tassie pans. Sprinkle walnuts in bottom of lined pans.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir the corn syrup, extract and egg into melted butter.
Spoon syrup mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes approximately 16.

title: coney sticks
directions: Cut rolls in fourths, lengthwise to make "fingers". Melt garlic spread and butter; brush on cut sides of rolls.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and poppy seed.	Place on cookie sheet and bake in very hot oven at 450° for 5 to 8 minutes or until toasty. Serve hot. Makes 24 sticks.

title: no cook macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter and pour into pan or casserole.
Stir uncooked macaroni into butter.
Cube cheese.
Add salt, pepper, cheese and milk to macaroni.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir while baking.
Use a 2-quart casserole or 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: granola
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients (dry).
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over dry mixture; mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven, until dry and crunchy, about 30 to 45 minutes, checking frequently.
After cooking, remove from oven; spread or gather into balls.
Form bars.
Refrigerate.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat well; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in dates and pecans.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 300° (start cake in cool oven).
Makes 1 (3 pound) cake.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You also need 24 cupcake liners.

title: karyn's layered pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 Tbsp. half and half and sugar in a large bowl with whisk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip and spread in crust.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with vegetable oil cooking spray. Put the cake mix in a large bowl and add the salad dressing, egg, cinnamon and 1/4 cup of water. Beat on low speed with an electric mixer just until blended. Stir in the carrots and walnuts. Pour the batter into the baking dish and bake for about 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean. When the cake is cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Put all of these into a crock-pot and cook on high for 1 hour and 4 hours on low.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: old time pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, spices, salt and pumpkin.
Next, add cream until well blended.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Good plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush 1/2 crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix chicken, sour cream and soup together.
Pour over crushed crackers.
Crush other 1/2 crackers and place on top of casserole.
Melt stick of oleo.
Pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cooked chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add milk to mix.
Add other ingredients except vanilla.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat with electric mixer until thick.
Add vanilla.

title: baked haddock
directions: Cut filets in serving pieces; place in greased shallow pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon, paprika, salt and pepper.
In saucepan melt butter, blend in flour, more salt and pepper.
Add milk, cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Pour sauce over filets; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: white shoe peg corn salad
directions: Drain
corn.
Dice cucumber, tomato and onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Sugar
and
salt should be added to taste.
Very good to use as a relish or slaw.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain fat and set aside.
Saute peppers, onions, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Season with lemon pepper, garlic salt and red pepper.
Drain butter.
In large pan, combine meat mixture and vegetables.
Add tomato sauce, paste and puree.
Add Italian seasoning to taste.
Bring to slow boil, reduce to simmer, stirring often.
Simmer to desired heat and flavor.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey, vanilla, dry milk, salt and sugar together.
Using your hands, shape into 1-inch balls and roll them in the peanuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cherry torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 6 egg whites stiff with 3/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Slowly add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in saltines and nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cooled torte with Cool Whip.
Spoon cherry pie filling over topping and chill 4 to 5 hours.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Mix and refrigerate up to 2 weeks.
Marinate meat at least 24 hours.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet on medium high heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to boiling point. Reduce to lowest heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serves 8. Serve with buttered saltines.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine Milky Way bars, margarine and pecans; heat until melted (cool).
Combine remaining ingredients; fold in candy mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Takes 3 (9-inch) pans.

title: peggy turner's pepper steak
directions: Cook steak in 1/2 tablespoon oleo, then add all other ingredients.
Mix well and cook 3 minutes more on low heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together, cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 6.

title: gooey butter squares
directions: Combine first four ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Then cream eggs and cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly add powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth and pour over first layer.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and ham salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard and lemon juice.
Mix in chicken, ham and celery.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Rub both sides of meat with garlic.
Roll meat in flour mixture.
Brown meat and onion in oleo in deep skillet.
Stir often.
Add soups and water.
Cook, uncovered, on low heat for 1 hour.
Stir this often.
Add mushrooms and sour cream, but do not boil.
Serve on rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: glenna's chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and spray 9X13 pan.

title: erma davis' cheese puffs
directions: Place
all
ingredients
in a bowl with fingers.
Blend all ingredients together until smooth.	Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Form into
1/2-inch
balls.
Flatten
with pecans if desired. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: To prepare watermelon rind:
Slice rind into uniform strips and remove any pink or green parts.
Cut into about 1-inch pieces. Dissolve the lime in 2 gallons cold water.
Soak rind overnight in cold water and lime.
Drain and rinse through two changes of cold water and soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Add the ginger to 1 gallon water, then add rind and boil 20 minutes.
Add sugar and sliced lemon to 3-quarts fresh water.
Bring to boiling, add rind and if desired, add spices (as above or to taste).
Cook until it is clear and tender.
Pack in clean, hot jars and seal immediately.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: russian tea
directions: Add all ingredients; mix well.
To make tea, add approximately 3 teaspoons to hot cup of water.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Soak oatmeal in milk for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in 2-quart greased casserole pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes, green pepper and onion.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender. Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: valentine's day punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cut oranges in slices to decorate bowl.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix these ingredients thoroughly.
Next, pack mixture into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan or into a 2-quart casserole.

title: williamsburg creamed celery
directions: Boil celery in a small amount of water until tender, then drain. Melt butter in a saucepan. Stir in flour, milk and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Add well drained celery. Spoon into a slightly greased 6-cup casserole dish. Top with pecan halves and cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cottage pie
directions: Brown beef in a frying pan.
Saute chopped onion and carrot in 1/2 the butter.
Dissolve bouillon cube in the boiling water.
Put all this in a pan and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mash boiled potatoes with rest of butter.
Add a little milk.
Place beef in casserole and cover with mashed potatoes.
Put under broiler to brown potatoes or store in refrigerator.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: best ever fried chicken
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first 4 ingredients. In a shallow bowl, combine the egg, milk and lemon juice. Place chicken pieces, one at a time, in the flour mixture; seal and shake to coat. Dip in the egg mixture and coat again with flour mixture. In an electric skillet or deep fat fryer, heat oil to 375°. Fry chicken, a few pieces at a time, for 6 to 10 minutes on each side or until juices run clear. Drain on paper towels. Serves 6 to 8.

title: amaretto-irish cream cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Press mixture evenly on bottom of a lightly greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: geebarnitza with phyllo dough
directions: Mix cheeses.
Add egg yolks and separately beaten egg whites. Add milk or cream to pouring consistency.
Melt butter.
Liberally coat a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread 4 sheets of phyllo dough in dish and brush with melted butter.
Spoon 1/4 of mixture into dish.
Cover with another 4 sheets of phyllo.
Brush with butter and repeat, ending with phyllo dough on top.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Cut small for appetizers.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and cook eggplant until tender and mash.
Cook meat, onion and bell pepper until done.
Mix meat mixture, eggplant, margarine, corn bread and enough milk to make real moist.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole and bake at 375° until brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: donna's apricot sherbet
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Chill all ingredients together, except half and half.
Add half and half.
Finish filling one gallon can with milk.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in water; debone and cut up.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in a greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or at 300° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except blueberries.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Bakes well in a 9 x 12-inch pan or in muffin pans.
Just adjust time.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Drain fruit well and combine all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: potato pie
directions: Put cottage cheese through food mill to make it smooth (this is not necessary if smooth consistency is not desired).
Beat in mashed potatoes (instant may be used).
Beat in sour cream, eggs, salt and cayenne pepper.
Stir in scallions.
Spoon into pie shell and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and slice 4 cups apples. Put in a bowl and sprinkle 2 cups sugar over the apples; set aside. Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add to apples. Mix 2 eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts to the apple mixture. Stir until well mixed. Batter will be dry. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix.
Sift together salt, soda and flour; add to mixture with 1 cup buttermilk, beating well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 or 9-inch) pans lined with wax paper, foil or floured and greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only with German Chocolate Icing.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Heat soup. Add sour cream, curry powder and cheese. Layer broccoli, chicken and sauce. Top with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Ice with remaining Cool Whip and refrigerate.
Shred Hershey bar on top.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cheese dip
directions: Pour can of Ro-Tel into small saucepan.
Add pepper.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Mix and serve with Tostados or Doritos. Serve dip hot or cold.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Simmer apples in juice concentrate until tender.
Add cornstarch (blended with a little water) and cinnamon.
Bake in double crust for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; sift twice.
Work in shortening with fingertips or pastry mixer.
Add liquid gradually, mixing with knife to make a soft dough.
Toss on floured board, pat down or knead a few minutes and roll lightly 3/4-inch thick. Shape with biscuit cutter.
Roll or pat mixture until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 4-inch squares.
Fill fruit with sugar mixed with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle with grated cheese or dot over with butter.
Draw 4 corners of dough together on top of fruit.
Pinch edges together.
Prick with fork and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maple cream pie
directions: Blend together 1/4 cup of the milk and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in remaining milk and 3/4 cup syrup and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Add butter.
Stir and cool.
Whip cream and add 1 cup to cooled filling.
Spoon into pie crust.
Add remaining syrup to whipped cream and spoon on pie.
Garnish with almonds.

title: country club chicken
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken. Coat well.
Melt butter in long Pyrex dish and place chicken in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: apple cobbler rolls
directions: Crust:
Mix shortening, flour and milk until stiff.
Roll on floured wax paper into a rectangle.

title: sour beef
directions: Marinate chuck in vinegar and water.
Put spices (next 7 ingredients) in bag and drop into mixture with meat.
Cover and let stand overnight or at least 24 hours.
Next day, cook remaining ingredients.
Remove meat from marinade; remove bag of spices. Cook marinade down to 1/2 its volume.
Sear meat on both sides and add the cooked down marinade to the gingersnap gravy.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cut it with a fork!

title: cheesy-cream of potato soup
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Peel potatoes and cut them into small cubes.
Add potatoes to onion and barely cover with hot water.
Season with garlic, salt and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until mushy.
Stir in can of soup.
Cut cheese into thin slices and stir into potato mixture.
Stir until cheese has melted.
Add milk.
May be served hot or cold.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to a paste like pie dough.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Mix other ingredients. Spread on baked crust.
Bake 22 minutes at 350°.

title: flavory fritters
directions: In a bowl beat eggs with milk, flour, baking powder, salt and 1 tablespoon of oil.
When smooth, fold in corn.
Pour enough oil into a large skillet to make it 1-inch deep and heat to 160°.
Drop in corn mixture by the heaping tablespoonful.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes until brown on one side.
Turn over and cook other side for 2 or 3 minutes until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and keep warm in low oven while finishing the rest of the frying.
Serve warm with sauteed pieces of Canadian bacon.

title: corn creole
directions: Saute green pepper
and
onion in butter.
Add meat and brown slightly.
Stir in
corn, beaten egg and milk.
Mix well and cook 5 minutes.
Add corn meal and seasonings.
Cook until the consistency of mush.
Pour
into a greased baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs
and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: rich roll cookies
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Chill dough 3 to 4 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll and cut out.
Bake on cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly browned.
Makes about 60 (2-inch) cookies.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill evaporated milk for 2 days.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add salt, honey, lemon juice and rind.
When slightly congealed, beat milk until stiff.
Whip gelatin into milk.
Spread half of crumbs on bottom of a buttered 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: blue mountain peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar together; form into little balls. Put a toothpick in each and freeze.
Once firm, then are ready to dip in chocolate.
Using a double boiler, put in both bags of chocolate morsels and the wax.
Melt well.
Dip balls into chocolate and cool on wax paper.
Twist off toothpicks and fill little holes with chocolate using the end of the toothpick.
Store in cool spot.
Cool well before serving.
Yields a lot!
Yummy!

title: pineapple corn bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar. Sift again. Add cornmeal.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine egg, milk, crushed pineapple and melted butter (slightly cooled).
Pour into flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Turn into a greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 50 minutes.

title: camp syrup
directions: Place all ingredients in a pan. Stir and cook until thickened. Sets up when cold; won't spill. Reheat at camp site or excellent at home on pancakes and waffles.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Serve with fruit. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: apple-almond upside-down pie
directions: Fix pastry for 2 (9-inch) pies.
Heat oven to 450°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with foil, letting foil hang over edge.
Spread with butter.
Press almonds into butter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Cover with pastry to make bottom crust.

title: shank bone soup
directions: Cook bones and meat until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Take out bones and meat.
Add rice, ground potatoes and onion to stock and boil.
Add tomato paste, salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until all ingredients are done.
Cut meat off bones and serve meat alongside or in soup.

title: "dolmathes" - stuffed grape leaves
directions: *Grape leaves may be bought at either an Italian or Greek import grocery.
Packed in glass jars, the more tender leaves usually come in the smaller jars (8 ounces as opposed to 12 ounces).

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use extra water if necessary to make mixture real soft so it will pour.
Pour into a greased baking pan about 3 inches deep, and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until well set and brown on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice raw potatoes into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Mix in green beans.
Crumble raw hamburg on top.
Dilute tomato soup with water; pour over the top.
Mix. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until done.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of small walnuts.
Flatten with cookie press. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: fred's dessert
directions: Mix margarine, nuts and flour and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until almost brown (about 20 minutes).
Cream the cream cheese and gradually beat in the powdered sugar.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread on the cooled crust.

title: chocolate cups for raspberry whip
directions: Melt chocolate.
Using cupcake papers, pour 1 1/2 teaspoons into each cup.
Using brush, paint cupcake papers and place in muffin tins and let sit until cool.
Peel papers carefully.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cheese and tomatoes.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers or vegetables.
Makes about 2 cups of dip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs and add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla, mixing well.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to the sugar mixture.
Mix well, until moist.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool before cutting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Beat well.
Mix in flour mixture thoroughly.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 2 1/2 loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Soften shortening or margarine.
Beat in brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix in chips and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 15 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together, then add 1 more can of drained Geisha tiny shrimp by spoon.
Serve in 1 big, round crusty bread; scoop out middle of bread so it looks like a bowl.
Cut inside pieces of bread in cubes and use to dip.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs and orange juice.
Spoon into greased and floured 8-inch pan. Top with brown sugar, cinnamon, grated orange rind, nuts and margarine.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage cheddar nuggets
directions: Combine all ingredients mixing well.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and lightly dust the inside with flour.
Cream together the butter and 2 cups of the sugar.
Add eggs, blending well, then the sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold the dry ingredients into the separate bowl.
Mix remaining 3/4 cup sugar with pecans and cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into the Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the pecan and sugar mixture.
Add remaining batter and top with the rest of the pecan mixture.
Set on the middle of the rack of the oven and bake for about 60 minutes, or until a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: gourmet chili
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper and all canned items in a large stew pot.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until bell pepper is soft.
Remove from heat.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add mixes, steak seasoning and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often for 10 minutes.
Combine everything into stew pot and cook on medium until hot.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients except raisins in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; mix well.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool; stir in raisins. Store in tightly covered container in dry place.
Serve as cereal with milk or as a snack.

title: butterscotch sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch or 9-inch layer pans or 13x9 in pan.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Add shortening, brown sugar, milk and flavoring.
Beat two minutes, medium speed on mixer.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly. add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into pans.
Bake 45-50 min. cool.
Frost with your favorite white icing.
Decorate with Butterscotch Glaze.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk and peanut butter well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least an hour.
An excellent summertime dessert!

title: italian beef
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until meat is tender. Slice or chip thin.
Put back in juice.
(Can be frozen or reheat and serve later.)
Serve on hard rolls.

title: ants on a log(child's recipe)
directions: Clean celery and cut in 4 sections.
Fill celery pieces with peanut butter and put 3 or more raisins on peanut butter.
Ready to serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: Put oil into 4-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave for 2 minutes at High.
Add meat; stir. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes at High; stir once.
Heat hot water in a 1-quart glass measuring cup in microwave to boiling (about 7 minutes).
Mix the flour, salt and pepper with meat.
Add boiling water, Worcestershire sauce, onion, carrots and potatoes; stir. Cover with a microwave-safe lid.
Cook in microwave for 70 to 85 minutes at Medium or until vegetables are tender.
Stir 3 times. Makes about 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and flour. Then add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into three (9-inch) pie shells. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the cucumbers, onions, green peppers and salt in a large bowl of ice water.
Let set for 3 hours.
Add all the spices in a pan.
Put on stove to boil.
Drain off the cucumbers from the water and add cucumbers to the spice mixture.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and form into balls.
Chill for 1 hour. Melt semi-sweet chocolate.
Put a few paraffin shavings in with the chocolate.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate.
Chill.

title: baked pork chops and vegetables
directions: Brown the pork chops in the fat in a skillet.
Remove chops and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add rice to chops.
Saute the onion and green pepper in the remaining fat in the skillet, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and black pepper to the onion and green pepper mixture.
Simmer until well blended. Pour the tomato mixture over the chops and rice.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour, or until tender.
